274  subroutine lak_create(packobj, id, ibcnum, inunit, iout, namemodel, pakname)
275 ! ******************************************************************************
276 ! lak_create -- Create a New LAKE Package
277 ! Subroutine: (1) create new-style package
278 ! (2) point bndobj to the new package
279 ! ******************************************************************************
280 !
281 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
282 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
283  class(bndtype), pointer :: packobj
284  integer(I4B),intent(in) :: id
285  integer(I4B),intent(in) :: ibcnum
286  integer(I4B),intent(in) :: inunit
287  integer(I4B),intent(in) :: iout
288  character(len=*), intent(in) :: namemodel
289  character(len=*), intent(in) :: pakname
290  type(laktype), pointer :: lakobj
291 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
292  !
293  ! -- allocate the object and assign values to object variables
294  allocate(lakobj)
295  packobj => lakobj
296  !
297  ! -- create name and memory path
298  call packobj%set_names(ibcnum, namemodel, pakname, ftype)
299  packobj%text = text
300  !
301  ! -- allocate scalars
302  call lakobj%lak_allocate_scalars()
303  !
304  ! -- initialize package
305  call packobj%pack_initialize()
306 
307  packobj%inunit = inunit
308  packobj%iout = iout
309  packobj%id = id
310  packobj%ibcnum = ibcnum
311  packobj%ncolbnd = 3
312  packobj%iscloc = 0 ! not supported
313  packobj%isadvpak = 1
314  packobj%ictMemPath = create_mem_path(namemodel,'NPF')
315  !
316  ! -- return
317  return
318  end subroutine lak_create

320  subroutine lak_allocate_scalars(this)
321 ! ******************************************************************************
322 ! allocate_scalars -- allocate scalar members
323 ! ******************************************************************************
324 !
325 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
326 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
327  ! -- dummy
328  class(laktype), intent(inout) :: this
329 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
330  !
331  ! -- call standard BndType allocate scalars

333  !

335  call mem_allocate(this%iprhed, 'IPRHED', this%memoryPath)

342  call mem_allocate(this%ntables, 'NTABLES', this%memoryPath)
343  call mem_allocate(this%convlength, 'CONVLENGTH', this%memoryPath)
344  call mem_allocate(this%convtime, 'CONVTIME', this%memoryPath)
345  call mem_allocate(this%outdmax, 'OUTDMAX', this%memoryPath)
346  call mem_allocate(this%igwhcopt, 'IGWHCOPT', this%memoryPath)
347  call mem_allocate(this%iconvchk, 'ICONVCHK', this%memoryPath)
348  call mem_allocate(this%iconvresidchk, 'ICONVRESIDCHK', this%memoryPath)
349  call mem_allocate(this%surfdep, 'SURFDEP', this%memoryPath)
350  call mem_allocate(this%delh, 'DELH', this%memoryPath)
351  call mem_allocate(this%pdmax, 'PDMAX', this%memoryPath)
352  call mem_allocate(this%check_attr, 'CHECK_ATTR', this%memoryPath)
353  call mem_allocate(this%bditems, 'BDITEMS', this%memoryPath)

356  !

359  this%istageout = 0
360  this%ibudgetout = 0
361  this%ibudcsv = 0
362  this%ipakcsv = 0

365  this%ntables = 0

383  subroutine lak_allocate_arrays(this)
384 ! ******************************************************************************
385 ! allocate_scalars -- allocate scalar members
386 ! ******************************************************************************
387 !
388 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
389 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
390  ! -- modules
391  ! -- dummy
392  class(laktype), intent(inout) :: this
393  ! -- local
394  integer(I4B) :: i
395 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
396  !
397  ! -- call standard BndType allocate scalars
398  call this%BndType%allocate_arrays()
399  !
400  ! -- allocate character array for budget text
401  allocate(this%clakbudget(this%bditems))
402  !
403  !-- fill clakbudget
404  this%clakbudget(1) = ' GWF'
405  this%clakbudget(2) = ' RAINFALL'
406  this%clakbudget(3) = ' EVAPORATION'
407  this%clakbudget(4) = ' RUNOFF'
408  this%clakbudget(5) = ' EXT-INFLOW'
409  this%clakbudget(6) = ' WITHDRAWAL'
410  this%clakbudget(7) = ' EXT-OUTFLOW'
411  this%clakbudget(8) = ' STORAGE'
412  this%clakbudget(9) = ' CONSTANT'
413  this%clakbudget(10) = ' FROM-MVR'
414  this%clakbudget(11) = ' TO-MVR'
415  !
416  ! -- allocate and initialize dbuff
417  if (this%istageout > 0) then
418  call mem_allocate(this%dbuff, this%nlakes, 'DBUFF', this%memoryPath)
419  do i = 1, this%nlakes
420  this%dbuff(i) = dzero
421  end do
422  else
423  call mem_allocate(this%dbuff, 0, 'DBUFF', this%memoryPath)
424  end if
425  !
426  ! -- allocate character array for budget text
427  allocate(this%cauxcbc(this%cbcauxitems))
428  !
429  ! -- allocate and initialize qauxcbc
430  call mem_allocate(this%qauxcbc, this%cbcauxitems, 'QAUXCBC', this%memoryPath)
431  do i = 1, this%cbcauxitems
432  this%qauxcbc(i) = dzero
433  end do
434  !
435  ! -- allocate qleak and qsto
436  call mem_allocate(this%qleak, this%maxbound, 'QLEAK', this%memoryPath)
437  do i = 1, this%maxbound
438  this%qleak(i) = dzero
439  end do
440  call mem_allocate(this%qsto, this%nlakes, 'QSTO', this%memoryPath)
441  do i = 1, this%nlakes
442  this%qsto(i) = dzero
443  end do
444  !
445  ! -- allocate denseterms to size 0
446  call mem_allocate(this%denseterms, 3, 0, 'DENSETERMS', this%memoryPath)
447  !
448  ! -- return
449  return
450  end subroutine lak_allocate_arrays

513  call mem_allocate(this%withr, this%nlakes, 'WITHR', this%memoryPath)
514  call mem_allocate(this%withr1, this%nlakes, 'WITHR1', this%memoryPath)
515  call mem_allocate(this%flwin, this%nlakes, 'FLWIN', this%memoryPath)
516  call mem_allocate(this%flwiter, this%nlakes, 'FLWITER', this%memoryPath)
517  call mem_allocate(this%flwiter1, this%nlakes, 'FLWITER1', this%memoryPath)
518  call mem_allocate(this%seep, this%nlakes, 'SEEP', this%memoryPath)
519  call mem_allocate(this%seep1, this%nlakes, 'SEEP1', this%memoryPath)
520  call mem_allocate(this%seep0, this%nlakes, 'SEEP0', this%memoryPath)
521  call mem_allocate(this%stageiter, this%nlakes, 'STAGEITER', this%memoryPath)
522  call mem_allocate(this%chterm, this%nlakes, 'CHTERM', this%memoryPath)
523  !
524  ! -- lake boundary and stages
525  call mem_allocate(this%iboundpak, this%nlakes, 'IBOUND', this%memoryPath)
526  call mem_allocate(this%xnewpak, this%nlakes, 'XNEWPAK', this%memoryPath)
527  call mem_allocate(this%xoldpak, this%nlakes, 'XOLDPAK', this%memoryPath)
528  !
529  ! -- lake iteration variables
530  call mem_allocate(this%iseepc, this%nlakes, 'ISEEPC', this%memoryPath)
531  call mem_allocate(this%idhc, this%nlakes, 'IDHC', this%memoryPath)
532  call mem_allocate(this%en1, this%nlakes, 'EN1', this%memoryPath)
533  call mem_allocate(this%en2, this%nlakes, 'EN2', this%memoryPath)
534  call mem_allocate(this%r1, this%nlakes, 'R1', this%memoryPath)
535  call mem_allocate(this%r2, this%nlakes, 'R2', this%memoryPath)
536  call mem_allocate(this%dh0, this%nlakes, 'DH0', this%memoryPath)
537  call mem_allocate(this%s0, this%nlakes, 'S0', this%memoryPath)
538  call mem_allocate(this%qgwf0, this%nlakes, 'QGWF0', this%memoryPath)
539  !
540  ! -- allocate character storage not managed by the memory manager
541  allocate(this%lakename(this%nlakes)) ! ditch after boundnames allocated??
542  allocate(this%status(this%nlakes))
543  !
544  do n = 1, this%nlakes
545  this%ntabrow(n) = 0
546  this%status(n) = 'ACTIVE'
547  this%laketop(n) = -dep20
548  this%lakebot(n) = dep20
549  this%sareamax(n) = dzero
550  this%iboundpak(n) = 1
551  this%xnewpak(n) = dep20
552  this%xoldpak(n) = dep20
553  !
554  ! -- initialize boundary values to zero
555  this%rainfall(n) = dzero
556  this%evaporation(n) = dzero
557  this%runoff(n) = dzero
558  this%inflow(n) = dzero
559  this%withdrawal(n) = dzero
560  end do
561  !
562  ! -- allocate local storage for aux variables
563  if (this%naux > 0) then
564  allocate(caux(this%naux))
565  end if
566  !
567  ! -- allocate and initialize temporary variables
568  allocate(nboundchk(this%nlakes))
569  do n = 1, this%nlakes
570  nboundchk(n) = 0
571  end do
572  !
573  ! -- read lake well data
574  ! -- get lakes block
575  call this%parser%GetBlock('PACKAGEDATA', isfound, ierr, &
576  supportopenclose=.true.)
577  !
578  ! -- parse locations block if detected
579  if (isfound) then
580  write(this%iout,'(/1x,a)') 'PROCESSING ' // trim(adjustl(this%text)) // &
581  ' PACKAGEDATA'
582  nlak = 0
583  nconn = 0
584  do
585  call this%parser%GetNextLine(endofblock)
586  if (endofblock) exit
587  n = this%parser%GetInteger()
588 
589  if (n < 1 .or. n > this%nlakes) then
590  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i6)') 'lakeno MUST BE > 0 and <= ', this%nlakes
591  call store_error(errmsg)
592  cycle
593  end if
594 
595  ! -- increment nboundchk
596  nboundchk(n) = nboundchk(n) + 1
597 
598  ! -- strt
599  this%strt(n) = this%parser%GetDouble()
600 
601  ! nlakeconn
602  ival = this%parser%GetInteger()
603 
604  if (ival < 0) then
605  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i6)') 'nlakeconn MUST BE >= 0 for lake ', n
606  call store_error(errmsg)
607  end if
608 
609  nconn = nconn + ival
610  this%nlakeconn(n) = ival
611 
612  ! -- get aux data
613  do iaux = 1, this%naux
614  call this%parser%GetString(caux(iaux))
615  end do
616 
617  ! -- set default bndName
618  write(cno,'(i9.9)') n
619  bndname = 'Lake' // cno
620 
621  ! -- lakename
622  if (this%inamedbound /= 0) then
623  call this%parser%GetStringCaps(bndnametemp)
624  if (bndnametemp /= '') then
625  bndname = bndnametemp
626  endif
627  end if
628  this%lakename(n) = bndname
629 
630  ! -- fill time series aware data
631  ! -- fill aux data
632  do jj = 1, this%naux
633  text = caux(jj)
634  ii = n
635  bndelem => this%lauxvar(jj, ii)
636  call read_value_or_time_series_adv(text, ii, jj, bndelem, this%packName, &
637  'AUX', this%tsManager, this%iprpak, &
638  this%auxname(jj))
639  end do
640 
641  nlak = nlak + 1
642  end do
643  !
644  ! -- check for duplicate or missing lakes
645  do n = 1, this%nlakes
646  if (nboundchk(n) == 0) then
647  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i0)') 'NO DATA SPECIFIED FOR LAKE', n
648  call store_error(errmsg)
649  else if (nboundchk(n) > 1) then
650  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i0,1x,a,1x,i0,1x,a)') &
651  'DATA FOR LAKE', n, 'SPECIFIED', nboundchk(n), 'TIMES'
652  call store_error(errmsg)
653  end if
654  end do
655 
656  write(this%iout,'(1x,a)') 'END OF ' // trim(adjustl(this%text)) // &
657  ' PACKAGEDATA'
658  else
659  call store_error('REQUIRED PACKAGEDATA BLOCK NOT FOUND.')
660  end if
661  !
662  ! -- terminate if any errors were detected
663  if (count_errors() > 0) then
664  call this%parser%StoreErrorUnit()
665  end if
666  !
667  ! -- set MAXBOUND
668  this%MAXBOUND = nconn
669  write(this%iout,'(//4x,a,i7)') 'MAXBOUND = ', this%maxbound
670 
671  ! -- set idxlakeconn
672  this%idxlakeconn(1) = 1
673  do n = 1, this%nlakes
674  this%idxlakeconn(n+1) = this%idxlakeconn(n) + this%nlakeconn(n)
675  end do
676  !
677  ! -- deallocate local storage for aux variables
678  if (this%naux > 0) then
679  deallocate(caux)
680  end if
681  !
682  ! -- deallocate local storage for nboundchk
683  deallocate(nboundchk)
684  !
685  ! -- return
686  return
687  end subroutine lak_read_lakes
688 
689  subroutine lak_read_lake_connections(this)
690 ! ******************************************************************************
691 ! lak_read_lake_connections -- Read the lake connections for this package
692 ! ******************************************************************************
693 !
694 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
695 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
696  use constantsmodule, only: linelength
697  use simmodule, only: store_error, count_errors
698  ! -- dummy
699  class(laktype),intent(inout) :: this
700  ! -- local
701  character(len=LINELENGTH) :: keyword, cellid
702  integer(I4B) :: ierr, ival
703  logical :: isfound, endOfBlock
704  real(DP) :: rval
705  integer(I4B) :: j, n
706  integer(I4B) :: nn
707  integer(I4B) :: ipos, ipos0
708  integer(I4B) :: icellid, icellid0
709  real(DP) :: top, bot
710  integer(I4B), dimension(:), pointer, contiguous :: nboundchk
711 
712  ! -- format
713  !
714  ! -- code
715  !
716  ! -- allocate local storage
717  allocate(nboundchk(this%MAXBOUND))
718  do n = 1, this%MAXBOUND
719  nboundchk(n) = 0
720  end do
721  !
722  ! -- get connectiondata block
723  call this%parser%GetBlock('CONNECTIONDATA', isfound, ierr, &
724  supportopenclose=.true.)
725  !
726  ! -- parse connectiondata block if detected
727  if (isfound) then
728 
729  ! -- allocate connection data using memory manager
730  call mem_allocate(this%imap, this%MAXBOUND, 'IMAP', this%memoryPath)
731  call mem_allocate(this%cellid, this%MAXBOUND, 'CELLID', this%memoryPath)
732  call mem_allocate(this%nodesontop, this%MAXBOUND, 'NODESONTOP', this%memoryPath)
733  call mem_allocate(this%ictype, this%MAXBOUND, 'ICTYPE', this%memoryPath)
734  call mem_allocate(this%bedleak, this%MAXBOUND, 'BEDLEAK', this%memoryPath) ! don't need to save this - use a temporary vector
735  call mem_allocate(this%belev, this%MAXBOUND, 'BELEV', this%memoryPath)
736  call mem_allocate(this%telev, this%MAXBOUND, 'TELEV', this%memoryPath)
737  call mem_allocate(this%connlength, this%MAXBOUND, 'CONNLENGTH', this%memoryPath)
738  call mem_allocate(this%connwidth, this%MAXBOUND, 'CONNWIDTH', this%memoryPath)
739  call mem_allocate(this%sarea, this%MAXBOUND, 'SAREA', this%memoryPath)
740  call mem_allocate(this%warea, this%MAXBOUND, 'WAREA', this%memoryPath)
741  call mem_allocate(this%satcond, this%MAXBOUND, 'SATCOND', this%memoryPath)
742  call mem_allocate(this%simcond, this%MAXBOUND, 'SIMCOND', this%memoryPath)
743  call mem_allocate(this%simlakgw, this%MAXBOUND, 'SIMLAKGW', this%memoryPath)
744 
745 
746  ! -- process the lake connection data
747  write(this%iout,'(/1x,a)')'PROCESSING '//trim(adjustl(this%text))// &
748  ' LAKE_CONNECTIONS'
749  do
750  call this%parser%GetNextLine(endofblock)
751  if (endofblock) exit
752  n = this%parser%GetInteger()
753 
754  if (n < 1 .or. n > this%nlakes) then
755  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i6)') 'lakeno MUST BE > 0 and <= ', this%nlakes
756  call store_error(errmsg)
757  cycle
758  end if
759 
760  ! -- read connection number
761  ival = this%parser%GetInteger()
762  if (ival < 1 .or. ival > this%nlakeconn(n)) then
763  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i4,1x,a,1x,i6)') &
764  'iconn FOR LAKE ', n, 'MUST BE > 1 and <= ', this%nlakeconn(n)
765  call store_error(errmsg)
766  cycle
767  end if
768 
769  j = ival
770  ipos = this%idxlakeconn(n) + ival - 1
771 
772  ! -- set imap
773  this%imap(ipos) = n
774 
775  !
776  ! -- increment nboundchk
777  nboundchk(ipos) = nboundchk(ipos) + 1
778 
779  ! -- read gwfnodes from the line
780  call this%parser%GetCellid(this%dis%ndim, cellid)
781  nn = this%dis%noder_from_cellid(cellid, &
782  this%parser%iuactive, this%iout)
783  !
784  ! -- determine if a valid cell location was provided
785  if (nn < 1) then
786  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i4,1x,a,1x,i4)') &
787  'INVALID cellid FOR LAKE ', n, 'connection', j
788  call store_error(errmsg)
789  end if
790 
791  ! -- set gwf cellid for connection
792  this%cellid(ipos) = nn
793  this%nodesontop(ipos) = nn
794 
795  ! -- read ictype
796  call this%parser%GetStringCaps(keyword)
797  select case (keyword)
798  case ('VERTICAL')
799  this%ictype(ipos) = 0
800  case ('HORIZONTAL')
801  this%ictype(ipos) = 1
802  case ('EMBEDDEDH')
803  this%ictype(ipos) = 2
804  case ('EMBEDDEDV')
805  this%ictype(ipos) = 3
806  case default
807  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i4,1x,a,1x,i4,1x,a,a,a)') &
808  'UNKNOWN ctype FOR LAKE ', n, 'connection', j, &
809  '(', trim(keyword), ')'
810  call store_error(errmsg)
811  end select
812 
813  ! -- bed leakance
814  !this%bedleak(ipos) = this%parser%GetDouble()
815  call this%parser%GetStringCaps(keyword)
816  select case(keyword)
817  case ('NONE')
818  this%bedleak(ipos) = -done
819  case default
820  read(keyword, *) this%bedleak(ipos)
821  end select
822 
823  if (keyword /= 'NONE' .and. this%bedleak(ipos) < dzero) then
824  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i4,1x,a)') 'bedleak FOR LAKE ', n, 'MUST BE >= 0'
825  call store_error(errmsg)
826  end if
827 
828  ! -- belev
829  this%belev(ipos) = this%parser%GetDouble()
830 
831  ! -- telev
832  this%telev(ipos) = this%parser%GetDouble()
833 
834  ! -- connection length
835  rval = this%parser%GetDouble()
836  if (rval < dzero) then
837  if (this%ictype(ipos) == 1 .or. this%ictype(ipos) == 2 .or. &
838  this%ictype(ipos) == 3) then
839  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i4,1x,a,1x,i4,1x,a)') &
840  'connection length (connlength) FOR LAKE ', n, &
841  ' HORIZONTAL CONNECTION ', j, 'MUST BE >= 0'
842  call store_error(errmsg)
843  else
844  rval = dzero
845  end if
846  end if
847  this%connlength(ipos) = rval
848 
849  ! -- connection width
850  rval = this%parser%GetDouble()
851  if (rval < dzero) then
852  if (this%ictype(ipos) == 1) then
853  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i4,1x,a,1x,i4,1x,a)') &
854  'cell width (connwidth) FOR LAKE ', n, &
855  ' HORIZONTAL CONNECTION ', j, 'MUST BE >= 0'
856  call store_error(errmsg)
857  else
858  rval = dzero
859  end if
860  end if
861  this%connwidth(ipos) = rval
862  end do
863  write(this%iout,'(1x,a)') &
864  'END OF '//trim(adjustl(this%text))//' CONNECTIONDATA'
865  else
866  call store_error('REQUIRED CONNECTIONDATA BLOCK NOT FOUND.')
867  end if
868  !
869  ! -- terminate if any errors were detected
870  if (count_errors() > 0) then
871  call this%parser%StoreErrorUnit()
872  end if
873  !
874  ! -- check that embedded lakes have only one connection
875  do n = 1, this%nlakes
876  j = 0
877  do ipos = this%idxlakeconn(n), this%idxlakeconn(n+1)-1
878  if (this%ictype(ipos) /= 2 .and. this%ictype(ipos) /= 3) cycle
879  j = j + 1
880  if (j > 1) then
881  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i4,1x,a,1x,i4,1x,a)') &
882  'nlakeconn FOR LAKE', n, 'EMBEDDED CONNECTION', j, ' EXCEEDS 1.'
883  call store_error(errmsg)
884  end if
885  end do
886  end do
887  ! -- check that an embedded lake is not in the same cell as a lake
888  ! with a vertical connection
889  do n = 1, this%nlakes
890  ipos0 = this%idxlakeconn(n)
891  icellid0 = this%cellid(ipos0)
892  if (this%ictype(ipos0) /= 2 .and. this%ictype(ipos0) /= 3) cycle
893  do nn = 1, this%nlakes
894  if (nn == n) cycle
895  j = 0
896  do ipos = this%idxlakeconn(nn), this%idxlakeconn(nn+1)-1
897  j = j + 1
898  icellid = this%cellid(ipos)
899  if (icellid == icellid0) then
900  if (this%ictype(ipos) == 0) then
901  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i4,1x,a,1x,i4,1x,a,1x,i4,1x,a)') &
902  'EMBEDDED LAKE', n, &
903  'CANNOT COINCIDE WITH VERTICAL CONNECTION', j, &
904  'IN LAKE', nn, '.'
905  call store_error(errmsg)
906  end if
907  end if
908  end do
909  end do
910  end do
911  !
912  ! -- process the data
913  do n = 1, this%nlakes
914  j = 0
915  do ipos = this%idxlakeconn(n), this%idxlakeconn(n+1)-1
916  j = j + 1
917  nn = this%cellid(ipos)
918  top = this%dis%top(nn)
919  bot = this%dis%bot(nn)
920  ! vertical connection
921  if (this%ictype(ipos) == 0) then
922  this%telev(ipos) = top + this%surfdep
923  this%belev(ipos) = top
924  this%lakebot(n) = min(this%belev(ipos), this%lakebot(n))
925  ! horizontal connection
926  else if (this%ictype(ipos) == 1) then
927  if (this%belev(ipos) == this%telev(ipos)) then
928  this%telev(ipos) = top
929  this%belev(ipos) = bot
930  else
931  if (this%belev(ipos) >= this%telev(ipos)) then
932  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i4,1x,a,1x,i4,1x,a)') &
933  'telev FOR LAKE ', n, ' HORIZONTAL CONNECTION ', j, &
934  'MUST BE >= belev'
935  call store_error(errmsg)
936  else if (this%belev(ipos) < bot) then
937  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i4,1x,a,1x,i4,1x,a,1x,g15.7,1x,a)') &
938  'belev FOR LAKE ', n, ' HORIZONTAL CONNECTION ', j, &
939  'MUST BE >= cell bottom (', bot, ')'
940  call store_error(errmsg)
941  else if (this%telev(ipos) > top) then
942  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i4,1x,a,1x,i4,1x,a,1x,g15.7,1x,a)') &
943  'telev FOR LAKE ', n, ' HORIZONTAL CONNECTION ', j, &
944  'MUST BE <= cell top (', top, ')'
945  call store_error(errmsg)
946  end if
947  end if
948  this%laketop(n) = max(this%telev(ipos), this%laketop(n))
949  this%lakebot(n) = min(this%belev(ipos), this%lakebot(n))
950  ! embedded connections
951  else if (this%ictype(ipos) == 2 .or. this%ictype(ipos) == 3) then
952  this%telev(ipos) = top
953  this%belev(ipos) = bot
954  this%lakebot(n) = bot
955  end if
956  !
957  ! -- check for missing or duplicate lake connections
958  if (nboundchk(ipos) == 0) then
959  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i0,1x,a,1x,i0)') &
960  'NO DATA SPECIFIED FOR LAKE', n, 'CONNECTION', j
961  call store_error(errmsg)
962  else if (nboundchk(ipos) > 1) then
963  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i0,1x,a,1x,i0,1x,a,1x,i0,1x,a)') &
964  'DATA FOR LAKE', n, 'CONNECTION', j, &
965  'SPECIFIED', nboundchk(ipos), 'TIMES'
966  call store_error(errmsg)
967  end if
968  !
969  ! -- set laketop if it has not been assigned
970  end do
971  if (this%laketop(n) == -dep20) then
972  this%laketop(n) = this%lakebot(n) + 100.
973  end if
974  end do
975  !
976  ! -- deallocate local variable
977  deallocate(nboundchk)
978  !
979  ! -- write summary of lake_connection error messages
980  if (count_errors() > 0) then
981  call this%parser%StoreErrorUnit()
982  end if
983  !
984  ! -- return
985  return
986  end subroutine lak_read_lake_connections
987 
988  subroutine lak_read_tables(this)
989 ! ******************************************************************************
990 ! lak_read_tables -- Read the lake tables for this package
991 ! ******************************************************************************
992 !
993 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
994 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
995  use constantsmodule, only: linelength
996  use simmodule, only: store_error, count_errors
997  ! -- dummy
998  class(laktype),intent(inout) :: this
999  ! -- local
1000  type (LakTabType), dimension(:), allocatable :: laketables
1001  character(len=LINELENGTH) :: line
1002  character(len=LINELENGTH) :: keyword
1003  integer(I4B) :: ierr
1004  logical :: isfound, endOfBlock
1005  integer(I4B) :: n
1006  integer(I4B) :: iconn
1007  integer(I4B) :: ntabs
1008  integer(I4B), dimension(:), pointer, contiguous :: nboundchk
1009 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1010 
1011  ! -- format
1012  !
1013  ! -- code
1014  !
1015  ! -- skip of no outlets
1016  if (this%ntables < 1) return
1017  !
1018  ! -- allocate and initialize nboundchk
1019  allocate(nboundchk(this%nlakes))
1020  do n = 1, this%nlakes
1021  nboundchk(n) = 0
1022  end do
1023  !
1024  ! -- allocate derived type for table data
1025  allocate(laketables(this%nlakes))
1026  !
1027  ! -- get lake_tables block
1028  call this%parser%GetBlock('TABLES', isfound, ierr, &
1029  supportopenclose=.true.)
1030  !
1031  ! -- parse lake_tables block if detected
1032  if (isfound) then
1033  ntabs = 0
1034  ! -- process the lake table data
1035  write(this%iout,'(/1x,a)')'PROCESSING '//trim(adjustl(this%text))// &
1036  ' LAKE_TABLES'
1037  readtable: do
1038  call this%parser%GetNextLine(endofblock)
1039  if (endofblock) exit
1040  n = this%parser%GetInteger()
1041 
1042  if (n < 1 .or. n > this%nlakes) then
1043  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i6)') 'lakeno MUST BE > 0 and <= ', this%nlakes
1044  call store_error(errmsg)
1045  cycle readtable
1046  end if
1047 
1048  ! -- increment ntab and nboundchk
1049  ntabs = ntabs + 1
1050  nboundchk(n) = nboundchk(n) + 1
1051 
1052  ! -- read FILE keyword
1053  call this%parser%GetStringCaps(keyword)
1054  select case (keyword)
1055  case('TAB6')
1056  call this%parser%GetStringCaps(keyword)
1057  if(trim(adjustl(keyword)) /= 'FILEIN') then
1058  errmsg = 'TAB6 keyword must be followed by "FILEIN" ' // &
1059  'then by filename.'
1060  call store_error(errmsg)
1061  cycle readtable
1062  end if
1063  call this%parser%GetString(line)
1064  call this%lak_read_table(n, line, laketables(n))
1065  case default
1066  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i4,1x,a)') &
1067  'LAKE TABLE ENTRY for LAKE ', n, 'MUST INCLUDE TAB6 KEYWORD'
1068  call store_error(errmsg)
1069  cycle readtable
1070  end select
1071  end do readtable
1072 
1073  write(this%iout,'(1x,a)') &
1074  'END OF ' // trim(adjustl(this%text)) // ' LAKE_TABLES'
1075  !
1076  ! -- check for missing or duplicate lake connections
1077  if (ntabs < this%ntables) then
1078  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i0,1x,a,1x,i0)') &
1079  'TABLE DATA ARE SPECIFIED', ntabs, &
1080  'TIMES BUT NTABLES IS SET TO', this%ntables
1081  call store_error(errmsg)
1082  end if
1083  do n = 1, this%nlakes
1084  if (this%ntabrow(n) > 0 .and. nboundchk(n) > 1) then
1085  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i0,1x,a,1x,i0,1x,a)') &
1086  'TABLE DATA FOR LAKE', n, 'SPECIFIED', nboundchk(n), 'TIMES'
1087  call store_error(errmsg)
1088  end if
1089  end do
1090  else
1091  call store_error('REQUIRED TABLES BLOCK NOT FOUND.')
1092  end if
1093  !
1094  ! -- deallocate local storage
1095  deallocate(nboundchk)
1096  !
1097  ! -- write summary of lake_table error messages
1098  if (count_errors() > 0) then
1099  call this%parser%StoreErrorUnit()
1100  end if
1101  !
1102  ! -- convert laketables to vectors
1103  call this%laktables_to_vectors(laketables)
1104  !
1105  ! -- destroy laketables
1106  do n = 1, this%nlakes
1107  if (this%ntabrow(n) > 0) then
1108  deallocate(laketables(n)%tabstage)
1109  deallocate(laketables(n)%tabvolume)
1110  deallocate(laketables(n)%tabsarea)
1111  iconn = this%idxlakeconn(n)
1112  if (this%ictype(iconn) == 2 .or. this%ictype(iconn) == 3) then
1113  deallocate(laketables(n)%tabwarea)
1114  end if
1115  end if
1116  end do
1117  deallocate(laketables)
1118  !
1119  ! -- return
1120  return
1121  end subroutine lak_read_tables

1123  subroutine laktables_to_vectors(this, laketables)
1124 ! ******************************************************************************
1125 ! laktables_to_vectors -- Copy the laketables structure data into flattened
1126 ! vectors that are stored in the memory manager
1127 ! ******************************************************************************
1128 !
1129 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
1130 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1131  class(laktype), intent(inout) :: this
1132  type (LakTabType), intent(in), dimension(:), contiguous :: laketables
1133  integer(I4B) :: n
1134  integer(I4B) :: ntabrows
1135  integer(I4B) :: j
1136  integer(I4B) :: ipos
1137  integer(I4B) :: iconn
1138 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1139  !
1140  ! -- allocate index array for lak tables
1141  call mem_allocate(this%ialaktab, this%nlakes + 1, 'IALAKTAB', this%memoryPath)
1142  !
1143  ! -- Move the laktables structure information into flattened arrays
1144  this%ialaktab(1) = 1
1145  do n = 1, this%nlakes
1146  ! -- ialaktab contains a pointer into the flattened lak table data
1147  this%ialaktab(n + 1) = this%ialaktab(n) + this%ntabrow(n)
1148  end do
1149  !
1150  ! -- Allocate vectors for storing all lake table data
1151  ntabrows = this%ialaktab(this%nlakes + 1) - 1
1152  call mem_allocate(this%tabstage, ntabrows, 'TABSTAGE', this%memoryPath)
1153  call mem_allocate(this%tabvolume, ntabrows, 'TABVOLUME', this%memoryPath)
1154  call mem_allocate(this%tabsarea, ntabrows, 'TABSAREA', this%memoryPath)
1155  call mem_allocate(this%tabwarea, ntabrows, 'TABWAREA', this%memoryPath)
1156  !
1157  ! -- Copy data from laketables into vectors
1158  do n = 1, this%nlakes
1159  j = 1
1160  do ipos = this%ialaktab(n), this%ialaktab(n + 1) - 1
1161  this%tabstage(ipos) = laketables(n)%tabstage(j)
1162  this%tabvolume(ipos) = laketables(n)%tabvolume(j)
1163  this%tabsarea(ipos) = laketables(n)%tabsarea(j)
1164  iconn = this%idxlakeconn(n)
1165  if (this%ictype(iconn) == 2 .or. this%ictype(iconn) == 3) then
1166  !
1167  ! -- tabwarea only filled for ictype 2 and 3
1168  this%tabwarea(ipos) = laketables(n)%tabwarea(j)
1169  else
1170  this%tabwarea(ipos) = dzero
1171  end if
1172  j = j + 1
1173  end do
1174  end do
1175  !
1176  ! -- return
1177  return
1178  end subroutine laktables_to_vectors

1180  subroutine lak_read_table(this, ilak, filename, laketable)
1181 ! ******************************************************************************
1182 ! lak_read_table -- Read the lake table for this package
1183 ! ******************************************************************************
1184 !
1185 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
1186 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1187  use constantsmodule, only: linelength
1188  use inputoutputmodule, only: openfile
1189  use simmodule, only: store_error, count_errors
1190  ! -- dummy
1191  class(laktype), intent(inout) :: this
1192  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: ilak
1193  character (len=*), intent(in) :: filename
1194  type (LakTabType), intent(inout) :: laketable
1195  ! -- local
1196  character(len=LINELENGTH) :: keyword
1197  integer(I4B) :: ierr
1198  logical :: isfound, endOfBlock
1199  integer(I4B) :: iu
1200  integer(I4B) :: n
1201  integer(I4B) :: ipos
1202  integer(I4B) :: j
1203  integer(I4B) :: jmin
1204  integer(I4B) :: iconn
1205  real(DP) :: vol
1206  real(DP) :: sa
1207  real(DP) :: wa
1208  real(DP) :: v
1209  real(DP) :: v0
1210  type(blockparsertype) :: parser
1211  ! -- formats
1212  character(len=*), parameter :: fmttaberr = &
1213  '(a,1x,i4,1x,a,1x,g15.6,1x,a,1x,i6,1x,a,1x,i4,1x,a,1x,g15.6,1x,a)'
1214 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1215 
1216  ! -- format
1217  !
1218  ! -- code
1219  !
1220  ! -- initialize locals
1221  n = 0
1222  j = 0
1223  !
1224  ! -- open the table file
1225  iu = 0
1226  call openfile(iu, this%iout, filename, 'LAKE TABLE')
1227  call parser%Initialize(iu, this%iout)
1228  !
1229  ! -- get dimensions block
1230  call parser%GetBlock('DIMENSIONS', isfound, ierr, supportopenclose=.true.)
1231  !
1232  ! -- parse lak table dimensions block if detected
1233  if (isfound) then
1234  ! -- process the lake table dimension data
1235  if (this%iprpak /= 0) then
1236  write(this%iout,'(/1x,a)') &
1237  'PROCESSING ' // trim(adjustl(this%text)) // ' DIMENSIONS'
1238  end if
1239  readdims: do
1240  call parser%GetNextLine(endofblock)
1241  if (endofblock) exit
1242  call parser%GetStringCaps(keyword)
1243  select case (keyword)
1244  case ('NROW')
1245  n = parser%GetInteger()
1246 
1247  if (n < 1) then
1248  write(errmsg,'(a)') 'LAKE TABLE NROW MUST BE > 0'
1249  call store_error(errmsg)
1250  end if
1251  case ('NCOL')
1252  j = parser%GetInteger()
1253 
1254  if (this%ictype(ilak) == 2 .or. this%ictype(ilak) == 3) then
1255  jmin = 4
1256  else
1257  jmin = 3
1258  end if
1259  if (j < jmin) then
1260  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i0)') 'LAKE TABLE NCOL MUST BE >= ', jmin
1261  call store_error(errmsg)
1262  end if
1263 
1264  case default
1265  write(errmsg,'(a,a)') &
1266  'UNKNOWN '//trim(this%text)//' DIMENSIONS KEYWORD: ', trim(keyword)
1267  call store_error(errmsg)
1268  end select
1269  end do readdims
1270  if (this%iprpak /= 0) then
1271  write(this%iout,'(1x,a)') &
1272  'END OF ' // trim(adjustl(this%text)) // ' DIMENSIONS'
1273  end if
1274  else
1275  call store_error('REQUIRED DIMENSIONS BLOCK NOT FOUND.')
1276  end if
1277  !
1278  ! -- check that ncol and nrow have been specified
1279  if (n < 1) then
1280  write(errmsg,'(a)') &
1281  'NROW NOT SPECIFIED IN THE LAKE TABLE DIMENSIONS BLOCK'
1282  call store_error(errmsg)
1283  end if
1284  if (j < 1) then
1285  write(errmsg,'(a)') &
1286  'NCOL NOT SPECIFIED IN THE LAKE TABLE DIMENSIONS BLOCK'
1287  call store_error(errmsg)
1288  end if
1289  !
1290  ! -- only read the lake table data if n and j are specified to be greater
1291  ! than zero
1292  if (n * j > 0) then
1293  !
1294  ! -- allocate space
1295  this%ntabrow(ilak) = n
1296  allocate(laketable%tabstage(n))
1297  allocate(laketable%tabvolume(n))
1298  allocate(laketable%tabsarea(n))
1299  ipos = this%idxlakeconn(ilak)
1300  if (this%ictype(ipos) == 2 .or. this%ictype(ipos) == 3) then
1301  allocate(laketable%tabwarea(n))
1302  end if
1303 
1304  ! -- get table block
1305  call parser%GetBlock('TABLE', isfound, ierr, supportopenclose=.true.)
1306  !
1307  ! -- parse well_connections block if detected
1308  if (isfound) then
1309 
1310  ! -- process the table data
1311  if (this%iprpak /= 0) then
1312  write(this%iout,'(/1x,a)') &
1313  'PROCESSING '//trim(adjustl(this%text))//' TABLE'
1314  end if
1315  iconn = this%idxlakeconn(ilak)
1316  ipos = 0
1317  readtabledata: do
1318  call parser%GetNextLine(endofblock)
1319  if (endofblock) exit
1320  ipos = ipos + 1
1321  if (ipos > this%ntabrow(ilak)) then
1322  cycle readtabledata
1323  end if
1324  laketable%tabstage(ipos) = parser%GetDouble()
1325  laketable%tabvolume(ipos) = parser%GetDouble()
1326  laketable%tabsarea(ipos) = parser%GetDouble()
1327  if (this%ictype(iconn) == 2 .or. this%ictype(iconn) == 3) then
1328  laketable%tabwarea(ipos) = parser%GetDouble()
1329  end if
1330  end do readtabledata
1331 
1332  if (this%iprpak /= 0) then
1333  write(this%iout,'(1x,a)') &
1334  'END OF '//trim(adjustl(this%text))//' TABLE'
1335  end if
1336  else
1337  call store_error('REQUIRED TABLE BLOCK NOT FOUND.')
1338  end if
1339  !
1340  ! -- error condition if number of rows read are not equal to nrow
1341  if (ipos /= this%ntabrow(ilak)) then
1342  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i0,1x,a,1x,i0,1x,a)') &
1343  'NROW SET TO', this%ntabrow(ilak), 'BUT', ipos, 'ROWS WERE READ'
1344  call store_error(errmsg)
1345  end if
1346  !
1347  ! -- set lake bottom based on table if it is an embedded lake
1348  iconn = this%idxlakeconn(ilak)
1349  if (this%ictype(iconn) == 2 .or. this%ictype(iconn) == 3) then
1350  do n = 1, this%ntabrow(ilak)
1351  vol = laketable%tabvolume(n)
1352  sa = laketable%tabsarea(n)
1353  wa = laketable%tabwarea(n)
1354  vol = vol * sa * wa
1355  ! -- check if all entries are zero
1356  if (vol > dzero) exit
1357  ! -- set lake bottom
1358  this%lakebot(ilak) = laketable%tabstage(n)
1359  this%belev(ilak) = laketable%tabstage(n)
1360  end do
1361  ! -- set maximum surface area for rainfall
1362  n = this%ntabrow(ilak)
1363  this%sareamax(ilak) = laketable%tabsarea(n)
1364  end if
1365  !
1366  ! -- verify the table data
1367  do n = 2, this%ntabrow(ilak)
1368  v = laketable%tabstage(n)
1369  v0 = laketable%tabstage(n-1)
1370  if (v <= v0) then
1371  write(errmsg,fmttaberr) &
1372  'TABLE STAGE ENTRY', n, '(', laketable%tabstage(n), &
1373  ') FOR LAKE ', ilak, 'MUST BE GREATER THAN THE PREVIOUS STAGE ENTRY',&
1374  n-1, '(', laketable%tabstage(n-1), ')'
1375  call store_error(errmsg)
1376  end if
1377  v = laketable%tabvolume(n)
1378  v0 = laketable%tabvolume(n-1)
1379  if (v <= v0) then
1380  write(errmsg,fmttaberr) &
1381  'TABLE VOLUME ENTRY', n, '(', laketable%tabvolume(n), &
1382  ') FOR LAKE ', &
1383  ilak, 'MUST BE GREATER THAN THE PREVIOUS VOLUME ENTRY', &
1384  n-1, '(', laketable%tabvolume(n-1), ')'
1385  call store_error(errmsg)
1386  end if
1387  v = laketable%tabsarea(n)
1388  v0 = laketable%tabsarea(n-1)
1389  if (v < v0) then
1390  write(errmsg,fmttaberr) &
1391  'TABLE SURFACE AREA ENTRY', n, '(', &
1392  laketable%tabsarea(n), ') FOR LAKE ', ilak, &
1393  'MUST BE GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO THE PREVIOUS SURFACE AREA ENTRY', &
1394  n-1, '(', laketable%tabsarea(n-1), ')'
1395  call store_error(errmsg)
1396  end if
1397  iconn = this%idxlakeconn(ilak)
1398  if (this%ictype(iconn) == 2 .or. this%ictype(iconn) == 3) then
1399  v = laketable%tabwarea(n)
1400  v0 = laketable%tabwarea(n-1)
1401  if (v < v0) then
1402  write(errmsg,fmttaberr) &
1403  'TABLE EXCHANGE AREA ENTRY', n, '(', &
1404  laketable%tabwarea(n), ') FOR LAKE ', ilak, &
1405  'MUST BE GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO THE PREVIOUS EXCHANGE AREA ' // &
1406  'ENTRY', n-1, '(', laketable%tabwarea(n-1), ')'
1407  call store_error(errmsg)
1408  end if
1409  end if
1410  end do
1411  end if
1412  !
1413  ! -- write summary of lake table error messages
1414  if (count_errors() > 0) then
1415  call parser%StoreErrorUnit()
1416  end if
1417  !
1418  ! Close the table file and clear other parser members
1419  call parser%Clear()
1420  !
1421  ! -- return
1422  return
1423  end subroutine lak_read_table

1425  subroutine lak_read_outlets(this)
1426 ! ******************************************************************************
1427 ! lak_read_outlets -- Read the lake outlets for this package
1428 ! ******************************************************************************
1429 !
1430 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
1431 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1432  use constantsmodule, only: linelength
1433  use simmodule, only: store_error, count_errors
1434  use timeseriesmanagermodule, only: read_value_or_time_series_adv
1435  ! -- dummy
1436  class(laktype),intent(inout) :: this
1437  ! -- local
1438  character(len=LINELENGTH) :: text, keyword
1439  character(len=LENBOUNDNAME) :: bndName
1440  character(len=9) :: citem
1441  integer(I4B) :: ierr, ival
1442  logical :: isfound, endOfBlock
1443  integer(I4B) :: n
1444  integer(I4B) :: jj
1445  integer(I4B), dimension(:), pointer, contiguous :: nboundchk
1446  real(DP), pointer :: bndElem => null()
1447  !
1448  ! -- format
1449  !
1450  ! -- code
1451 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1452  !
1453  ! -- get well_connections block
1454  call this%parser%GetBlock('OUTLETS', isfound, ierr, &
1455  supportopenclose=.true., blockrequired=.false.)
1456  !
1457  ! -- parse outlets block if detected
1458  if (isfound) then
1459  if (this%noutlets > 0) then
1460  !
1461  ! -- allocate and initialize local variables
1462  allocate(nboundchk(this%noutlets))
1463  do n = 1, this%noutlets
1464  nboundchk(n) = 0
1465  end do
1466  !
1467  ! -- allocate outlet data using memory manager
1468  call mem_allocate(this%lakein, this%NOUTLETS, 'LAKEIN', this%memoryPath)
1469  call mem_allocate(this%lakeout, this%NOUTLETS, 'LAKEOUT', this%memoryPath)
1470  call mem_allocate(this%iouttype, this%NOUTLETS, 'IOUTTYPE', this%memoryPath)
1471  call mem_allocate(this%outrate, this%NOUTLETS, 'OUTRATE', this%memoryPath)
1472  call mem_allocate(this%outinvert, this%NOUTLETS, 'OUTINVERT', &
1473  this%memoryPath)
1474  call mem_allocate(this%outwidth, this%NOUTLETS, 'OUTWIDTH', this%memoryPath)
1475  call mem_allocate(this%outrough, this%NOUTLETS, 'OUTROUGH', this%memoryPath)
1476  call mem_allocate(this%outslope, this%NOUTLETS, 'OUTSLOPE', this%memoryPath)
1477  call mem_allocate(this%simoutrate, this%NOUTLETS, 'SIMOUTRATE', &
1478  this%memoryPath)
1479  !
1480  ! -- initialize outlet rate
1481  do n = 1, this%noutlets
1482  this%outrate(n) = dzero
1483  end do
1484 
1485  ! -- process the lake connection data
1486  write(this%iout,'(/1x,a)') &
1487  'PROCESSING ' // trim(adjustl(this%text)) // ' OUTLETS'
1488  readoutlet: do
1489  call this%parser%GetNextLine(endofblock)
1490  if (endofblock) exit
1491  n = this%parser%GetInteger()
1492 
1493  if (n < 1 .or. n > this%noutlets) then
1494  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i6)') &
1495  'outletno MUST BE > 0 and <= ', this%noutlets
1496  call store_error(errmsg)
1497  cycle readoutlet
1498  end if
1499  !
1500  ! -- increment nboundchk
1501  nboundchk(n) = nboundchk(n) + 1
1502  !
1503  ! -- read outlet lakein
1504  ival = this%parser%GetInteger()
1505  if (ival <1 .or. ival > this%nlakes) then
1506  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i4,1x,a,1x,i6)') &
1507  'lakein FOR OUTLET ', n, 'MUST BE > 0 and <= ', this%nlakes
1508  call store_error(errmsg)
1509  cycle readoutlet
1510  end if
1511  this%lakein(n) = ival
1512 
1513  ! -- read outlet lakeout
1514  ival = this%parser%GetInteger()
1515  if (ival <0 .or. ival > this%nlakes) then
1516  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i4,1x,a,1x,i6)') &
1517  'lakeout FOR OUTLET ', n, 'MUST BE >= 0 and <= ', this%nlakes
1518  call store_error(errmsg)
1519  cycle readoutlet
1520  end if
1521  this%lakeout(n) = ival
1522 
1523  ! -- read ictype
1524  call this%parser%GetStringCaps(keyword)
1525  select case (keyword)
1526  case ('SPECIFIED')
1527  this%iouttype(n) = 0
1528  case ('MANNING')
1529  this%iouttype(n) = 1
1530  case ('WEIR')
1531  this%iouttype(n) = 2
1532  case default
1533  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i4,1x,a,a,a)') &
1534  'UNKNOWN couttype FOR OUTLET ', n, '(', trim(keyword), ')'
1535  call store_error(errmsg)
1536  cycle readoutlet
1537  end select
1538 
1539  ! -- build bndname for outlet
1540  write(citem,'(i9.9)') n
1541  bndname = 'OUTLET' // citem
1542 
1543  ! -- set a few variables for timeseries aware variables
1544  jj = 1
1545  !
1546  ! -- outlet invert
1547  call this%parser%GetString(text)
1548  bndelem => this%outinvert(n)
1549  call read_value_or_time_series_adv(text, n, jj, bndelem, this%packName, &
1550  'BND', this%tsManager, this%iprpak, &
1551  'INVERT')
1552  !
1553  ! -- outlet width
1554  call this%parser%GetString(text)
1555  bndelem => this%outwidth(n)
1556  call read_value_or_time_series_adv(text, n, jj, bndelem, this%packName, &
1557  'BND', this%tsManager, this%iprpak, &
1558  'WIDTH')
1559  !
1560  ! -- outlet roughness
1561  call this%parser%GetString(text)
1562  bndelem => this%outrough(n)
1563  call read_value_or_time_series_adv(text, n, jj, bndelem, this%packName, &
1564  'BND', this%tsManager, this%iprpak, &
1565  'ROUGH')
1566  !
1567  ! -- outlet slope
1568  call this%parser%GetString(text)
1569  bndelem => this%outslope(n)
1570  call read_value_or_time_series_adv(text, n, jj, bndelem, this%packName, &
1571  'BND', this%tsManager, this%iprpak, &
1572  'SLOPE')
1573  end do readoutlet
1574  write(this%iout,'(1x,a)') 'END OF ' // trim(adjustl(this%text)) // &
1575  ' OUTLETS'
1576  !
1577  ! -- check for duplicate or missing outlets
1578  do n = 1, this%noutlets
1579  if (nboundchk(n) == 0) then
1580  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i0)') 'NO DATA SPECIFIED FOR OUTLET', n
1581  call store_error(errmsg)
1582  else if (nboundchk(n) > 1) then
1583  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,i0,1x,a,1x,i0,1x,a)') &
1584  'DATA FOR OUTLET', n, 'SPECIFIED', nboundchk(n), 'TIMES'
1585  call store_error(errmsg)
1586  end if
1587  end do
1588  !
1589  ! -- deallocate local storage
1590  deallocate(nboundchk)
1591  else
1592  write(errmsg,'(a,1x,a)') &
1593  'AN OUTLETS BLOCK SHOULD NOT BE SPECIFIED IF NOUTLETS IS NOT', &
1594  'SPECIFIED OR IS SPECIFIED TO BE 0.'
1595  call store_error(errmsg)
1596  end if
1597 
1598  else
1599  if (this%noutlets > 0) then
1600  call store_error('REQUIRED OUTLETS BLOCK NOT FOUND.')
1601  end if
1602  end if
1603  !
1604  ! -- write summary of lake_connection error messages
1605  ierr = count_errors()
1606  if (ierr > 0) then
1607  call this%parser%StoreErrorUnit()
1608  end if
1609  !
1610  ! -- return
1611  return
1612  end subroutine lak_read_outlets

1614  subroutine lak_read_dimensions(this)
1615 ! ******************************************************************************
1616 ! pak1read_dimensions -- Read the dimensions for this package
1617 ! ******************************************************************************
1618 !
1619 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
1620 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1621  use constantsmodule, only: linelength
1622  use simmodule, only: store_error, count_errors
1623  ! -- dummy
1624  class(laktype),intent(inout) :: this
1625  ! -- local
1626  character(len=LINELENGTH) :: keyword
1627  integer(I4B) :: ierr
1628  logical :: isfound, endOfBlock
1629  ! -- format
1630 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1631  !
1632  ! -- initialize dimensions to -1
1633  this%nlakes= -1
1634  this%maxbound = -1
1635  !
1636  ! -- get dimensions block

1639  !

1647  call this%parser%GetStringCaps(keyword)

1658  case default

1660  'UNKNOWN '//trim(this%text)//' DIMENSION: ', trim(keyword)

1662  end select
1663  end do
1664  write(this%iout,'(1x,a)') &
1665  'END OF ' // trim(adjustl(this%text)) // ' DIMENSIONS'
1666  else

1708  subroutine lak_read_initial_attr(this)
1709 ! ******************************************************************************
1710 ! pak1read_dimensions -- Read the initial parameters for this package
1711 ! ******************************************************************************
1712 !
1713 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
1714 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1715  use constantsmodule, only: linelength
1716  use memoryhelpermodule, only: create_mem_path
1717  use simmodule, only: store_error, count_errors
1718  use timeseriesmanagermodule, only: read_value_or_time_series_adv
1719  ! -- dummy
1720  class(laktype),intent(inout) :: this
1721  ! -- local
1722  character(len=LINELENGTH) :: text
1723  integer(I4B) :: j, jj, n
1724  integer(I4B) :: nn
1725  integer(I4B) :: idx
1726  real(DP) :: top
1727  real(DP) :: bot
1728  real(DP) :: k
1729  real(DP) :: area
1730  real(DP) :: length
1731  real(DP) :: s
1732  real(DP) :: dx
1733  real(DP) :: c
1734  real(DP) :: sa
1735  real(DP) :: wa
1736  real(DP) :: v
1737  real(DP) :: fact
1738  real(DP) :: c1
1739  real(DP) :: c2
1740  real(DP), allocatable, dimension(:) :: clb, caq
1741  character (len=14) :: cbedleak
1742  character (len=14) :: cbedcond
1743  character (len=10), dimension(0:3) :: ctype
1744  character (len=15) :: nodestr
1745  real(DP), pointer :: bndElem => null()
1746  ! -- data
1747  data ctype(0) /'VERTICAL '/
1748  data ctype(1) /'HORIZONTAL'/
1749  data ctype(2) /'EMBEDDEDH '/
1750  data ctype(3) /'EMBEDDEDV '/
1751  ! -- format
1752 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1753  !
1754  ! -- initialize xnewpak and set stage
1755  do n = 1, this%nlakes
1756  this%xnewpak(n) = this%strt(n)
1757  write(text,'(g15.7)') this%strt(n)
1758  jj = 1 ! For STAGE
1759  bndelem => this%stage(n)
1760  call read_value_or_time_series_adv(text, n, jj, bndelem, this%packName, 'BND', &
1761  this%tsManager, this%iprpak, &
1762  'STAGE')
1763  end do
1764  !
1765  ! -- initialize status (iboundpak) of lakes to active
1766  do n = 1, this%nlakes
1767  if (this%status(n) == 'CONSTANT') then
1768  this%iboundpak(n) = -1
1769  else if (this%status(n) == 'INACTIVE') then
1770  this%iboundpak(n) = 0
1771  else if (this%status(n) == 'ACTIVE ') then
1772  this%iboundpak(n) = 1
1773  end if
1774  end do
1775  !
1776  ! -- set boundname for each connection
1777  if (this%inamedbound /= 0) then
1778  do n = 1, this%nlakes
1779  do j = this%idxlakeconn(n), this%idxlakeconn(n+1)-1
1780  this%boundname(j) = this%lakename(n)
1781  end do
1782  end do
1783  endif
1784  !
1785  ! -- set pointer to gwf iss and gwf hk
1786  call mem_setptr(this%gwfiss, 'ISS', create_mem_path(this%name_model))
1787  call mem_setptr(this%gwfk11, 'K11', create_mem_path(this%name_model, 'NPF'))
1788  call mem_setptr(this%gwfk33, 'K33', create_mem_path(this%name_model, 'NPF'))
1789  call mem_setptr(this%gwfik33, 'IK33', create_mem_path(this%name_model, 'NPF'))
1790  call mem_setptr(this%gwfsat, 'SAT', create_mem_path(this%name_model, 'NPF'))
1791  !
1792  ! -- allocate temporary storage
1793  allocate(clb(this%MAXBOUND))
1794  allocate(caq(this%MAXBOUND))
1795 
1796  ! -- calculate saturated conductance for each connection
1797  do n = 1, this%nlakes
1798  do j = this%idxlakeconn(n), this%idxlakeconn(n+1)-1
1799  nn = this%cellid(j)
1800  top = this%dis%top(nn)
1801  bot = this%dis%bot(nn)
1802  ! vertical connection
1803  if (this%ictype(j) == 0) then
1804  area = this%dis%area(nn)
1805  this%sarea(j) = area
1806  this%warea(j) = area
1807  this%sareamax(n) = this%sareamax(n) + area
1808  if (this%gwfik33 == 0) then
1809  k = this%gwfk11(nn)
1810  else
1811  k = this%gwfk33(nn)
1812  endif
1813  length = dhalf * (top - bot)
1814  ! horizontal connection
1815  else if (this%ictype(j) == 1) then
1816  area = (this%telev(j) - this%belev(j)) * this%connwidth(j)
1817  ! -- recalculate area if connected cell is confined and lake
1818  ! connection top and bot are equal to the cell top and bot
1819  if (top == this%telev(j) .and. bot == this%belev(j)) then
1820  if (this%icelltype(nn) == 0) then
1821  area = this%gwfsat(nn) * (top - bot) * this%connwidth(j)
1822  end if
1823  end if
1824  this%sarea(j) = dzero
1825  this%warea(j) = area
1826  this%sareamax(n) = this%sareamax(n) + dzero
1827  k = this%gwfk11(nn)
1828  length = this%connlength(j)
1829  ! embedded horizontal connection
1830  else if (this%ictype(j) == 2) then
1831  area = done
1832  this%sarea(j) = dzero
1833  this%warea(j) = area
1834  this%sareamax(n) = this%sareamax(n) + dzero
1835  k = this%gwfk11(nn)
1836  length = this%connlength(j)
1837  ! embedded vertical connection
1838  else if (this%ictype(j) == 3) then
1839  area = done
1840  this%sarea(j) = dzero
1841  this%warea(j) = area
1842  this%sareamax(n) = this%sareamax(n) + dzero
1843  if (this%gwfik33 == 0) then
1844  k = this%gwfk11(nn)
1845  else
1846  k = this%gwfk33(nn)
1847  endif
1848  length = this%connlength(j)
1849  end if
1850  if (this%bedleak(j) < dzero) then
1851  clb(j) = -done
1852  else if (this%bedleak(j) > dzero) then
1853  clb(j) = done / this%bedleak(j)
1854  else
1855  clb(j) = dzero
1856  end if
1857  if (k > dzero) then
1858  caq(j) = length / k
1859  else
1860  caq(j) = dzero
1861  end if
1862  if (this%bedleak(j) < dzero) then
1863  this%satcond(j) = area / caq(j)
1864  else if (clb(j)*caq(j) > dzero) then
1865  this%satcond(j) = area / (clb(j) + caq(j))
1866  else
1867  this%satcond(j) = dzero
1868  end if
1869  end do
1870  end do
1871  !
1872  ! -- write a summary of the conductance
1873  if (this%iprpak > 0) then
1874  write(this%iout,'(//,29x,a,/)') 'INTERFACE CONDUCTANCE BETWEEN LAKE AND AQUIFER CELLS'
1875  write(this%iout,'(1x,a)') &
1876  & ' LAKE CONNECTION CONNECTION LAKEBED' // &
1877  & ' C O N D U C T A N C E S '
1878  write(this%iout,'(1x,a)') &
1879  & ' NUMBER NUMBER CELLID DIRECTION LEAKANCE' // &
1880  & ' LAKEBED AQUIFER COMBINED'
1881  write(this%iout,"(1x,108('-'))")
1882  do n = 1, this%nlakes
1883  idx = 0
1884  do j = this%idxlakeconn(n), this%idxlakeconn(n+1)-1
1885  idx = idx + 1
1886  fact = done
1887  if (this%ictype(j) == 1) then
1888  fact = this%telev(j) - this%belev(j)
1889  if (abs(fact) > dzero) then
1890  fact = done / fact
1891  end if
1892  end if
1893  nn = this%cellid(j)
1894  area = this%warea(j)
1895  c1 = dzero
1896  if (clb(j) < dzero) then
1897  cbedleak = ' NONE '
1898  cbedcond = ' NONE '
1899  else if (clb(j) > dzero) then
1900  c1 = area * fact / clb(j)
1901  write(cbedleak,'(g14.5)') this%bedleak(j)
1902  write(cbedcond,'(g14.5)') c1
1903  else
1904  write(cbedleak,'(g14.5)') c1
1905  write(cbedcond,'(g14.5)') c1
1906  end if
1907  c2 = dzero
1908  if (caq(j) > dzero) then
1909  c2 = area * fact / caq(j)
1910  end if
1911  call this%dis%noder_to_string(nn, nodestr)
1912  write(this%iout,'(1x,i10,1x,i10,1x,a15,1x,a10,2(1x,a14),2(1x,g14.5))') &
1913  & n, idx, nodestr, ctype(this%ictype(j)), cbedleak, &
1914  & cbedcond, c2, this%satcond(j) * fact
1915  end do
1916  end do
1917  write(this%iout,"(1x,108('-'))")
1918  write(this%iout,'(1x,a)') 'IF VERTICAL CONNECTION, CONDUCTANCE (L^2/T) IS BETWEEN AQUIFER CELL AND OVERLYING LAKE CELL.'
1919  write(this%iout,'(1x,a)') 'IF HORIZONTAL CONNECTION, CONDUCTANCES ARE PER UNIT SATURATED THICKNESS (L/T).'
1920  write(this%iout,'(1x,a)') 'IF EMBEDDED CONNECTION, CONDUCTANCES ARE PER UNIT EXCHANGE AREA (1/T).'
1921 
1922  ! write(this%iout,*) n, idx, nodestr, this%sarea(j), this%warea(j)
1923  !
1924  ! -- calculate stage, surface area, wetted area, volume relation
1925  do n = 1, this%nlakes
1926  write(this%iout,'(//1x,a,1x,i10)') 'STAGE/VOLUME RELATION FOR LAKE ', n
1927  write(this%iout,'(/1x,5(a14))') ' STAGE', ' SURFACE AREA', &
1928  & ' WETTED AREA', ' CONDUCTANCE', &
1929  & ' VOLUME'
1930  write(this%iout,"(1x,70('-'))")
1931  dx = (this%laketop(n) - this%lakebot(n)) / 150.
1932  s = this%lakebot(n)
1933  do j = 1, 151
1934  call this%lak_calculate_conductance(n, s, c)
1935  call this%lak_calculate_sarea(n, s, sa)
1936  call this%lak_calculate_warea(n, s, wa, s)
1937  call this%lak_calculate_vol(n, s, v)
1938  write(this%iout,'(1x,5(E14.5))') s, sa, wa, c, v
1939  s = s + dx
1940  end do
1941  write(this%iout,"(1x,70('-'))")
1942 
1943  write(this%iout,'(//1x,a,1x,i10)') 'STAGE/VOLUME RELATION FOR LAKE ', n
1944  write(this%iout,'(/1x,4(a14))') ' ', ' ', &
1945  & ' CALCULATED', ' STAGE'
1946  write(this%iout,'(1x,4(a14))') ' STAGE', ' VOLUME', &
1947  & ' STAGE', ' DIFFERENCE'
1948  write(this%iout,"(1x,56('-'))")
1949  s = this%lakebot(n) - dx
1950  do j = 1, 156
1951  call this%lak_calculate_vol(n, s, v)
1952  call this%lak_vol2stage(n, v, c)
1953  write(this%iout,'(1x,4(E14.5))') s, v, c, s-c
1954  s = s + dx
1955  end do
1956  write(this%iout,"(1x,56('-'))")
1957  end do
1958  end if
1959  !
1960  ! -- finished with pointer to gwf hydraulic conductivity
1961  this%gwfk11 => null()
1962  this%gwfk33 => null()
1963  this%gwfsat => null()
1964  this%gwfik33 => null()
1965  !
1966  ! -- deallocate temporary storage
1967  deallocate(clb)
1968  deallocate(caq)
1969  !
1970  ! -- return
1971  return
1972  end subroutine lak_read_initial_attr

1974 ! -- simple subroutine for linear interpolation of two vectors
1975 ! function assumes x data is sorted in ascending order
1976  subroutine lak_linear_interpolation(this, n, x, y, z, v)
1977  ! -- dummy
1978  class(laktype),intent(inout) :: this
1979  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: n
1980  real(DP), dimension(n), intent(in) :: x
1981  real(DP), dimension(n), intent(in) :: y
1982  real(DP), intent(in) :: z
1983  real(DP), intent(inout) :: v
1984  ! -- local
1985  integer(I4B) :: i
1986  real(DP) :: dx, dydx
1987  ! code
1988  v = dzero
1989  ! below bottom of range - set to lowest value
1990  if (z <= x(1)) then
1991  v = y(1)
1992  ! above highest value
1993  ! slope calculated from interval between n and n-1
1994  else if (z > x(n)) then
1995  dx = x(n) - x(n-1)
1996  dydx = dzero
1997  if (abs(dx) > dzero) then
1998  dydx = ( y(n) - y(n-1) ) / dx
1999  end if
2000  dx = (z - x(n))
2001  v = y(n) + dydx * dx
2002  ! between lowest and highest value in current interval
2003  else
2004  do i = 2, n
2005  dx = x(i) - x(i-1)
2006  dydx = dzero
2007  if (z >= x(i-1) .and. z <= x(i)) then
2008  if (abs(dx) > dzero) then
2009  dydx = ( y(i) - y(i-1) ) / dx
2010  end if
2011  dx = (z - x(i-1))
2012  v = y(i-1) + dydx * dx
2013  exit
2014  end if
2015  end do
2016  end if
2017  ! return
2018  return
2019  end subroutine lak_linear_interpolation

2021  subroutine lak_calculate_sarea(this, ilak, stage, sarea)
2022 ! ******************************************************************************
2023 ! lak_calculate_sarea -- Calculate the surface area of a lake at a given stage.
2024 ! ******************************************************************************
2025 !
2026 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
2027 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2028  ! -- dummy
2029  class(laktype),intent(inout) :: this
2030  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: ilak
2031  real(DP), intent(in) :: stage
2032  real(DP), intent(inout) :: sarea
2033  ! -- local
2034  integer(I4B) :: i
2035  integer(I4B) :: ifirst
2036  integer(I4B) :: ilast
2037  real(DP) :: topl
2038  real(DP) :: botl
2039  real(DP) :: sat
2040  real(DP) :: sa
2041  ! -- formats
2042 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2043  sarea = dzero
2044  i = this%ntabrow(ilak)
2045  if (i > 0) then
2046  ifirst = this%ialaktab(ilak)
2047  ilast = this%ialaktab(ilak + 1) - 1
2048  if (stage <= this%tabstage(ifirst)) then
2049  sarea = this%tabsarea(ifirst)
2050  else if (stage >= this%tabstage(ilast)) then
2051  sarea = this%tabsarea(ilast)
2052  else
2053  call this%lak_linear_interpolation(i, this%tabstage(ifirst:ilast), &
2054  this%tabsarea(ifirst:ilast), &
2055  stage, sarea)
2056  end if
2057  else
2058  do i = this%idxlakeconn(ilak), this%idxlakeconn(ilak+1)-1
2059  topl = this%telev(i)
2060  botl = this%belev(i)
2061  sat = squadraticsaturation(topl, botl, stage)
2062  sa = sat * this%sarea(i)
2063  sarea = sarea + sa
2064  end do
2065  end if
2066  !
2067  ! -- return
2068  return
2069  end subroutine lak_calculate_sarea

2110 ! at a given stage.
2111 ! ******************************************************************************
2112 !

2157  else

2159  end if
2160  wa = sat * this%warea(iconn)
2161  end if

2168  subroutine lak_calculate_vol(this, ilak, stage, volume)
2169 ! ******************************************************************************
2170 ! lak_calculate_vol -- Calculate the volume of a lake at a given stage.
2171 ! ******************************************************************************
2172 !
2173 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
2174 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2175  ! -- dummy
2176  class(laktype),intent(inout) :: this
2177  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: ilak
2178  real(DP), intent(in) :: stage
2179  real(DP), intent(inout) :: volume
2180  ! -- local
2181  integer(I4B) :: i
2182  integer(I4B) :: ifirst
2183  integer(I4B) :: ilast
2184  real(DP) :: topl
2185  real(DP) :: botl
2186  real(DP) :: ds
2187  real(DP) :: sa
2188  real(DP) :: v
2189  real(DP) :: sat
2190  ! -- formats
2191 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2192  volume = dzero
2193  i = this%ntabrow(ilak)
2194  if (i > 0) then
2195  ifirst = this%ialaktab(ilak)
2196  ilast = this%ialaktab(ilak + 1) - 1
2197  if (stage <= this%tabstage(ifirst)) then
2198  volume = this%tabvolume(ifirst)
2199  else if (stage >= this%tabstage(ilast)) then
2200  ds = stage - this%tabstage(ilast)
2201  sa = this%tabsarea(ilast)
2202  volume = this%tabvolume(ilast) + ds * sa
2203  else
2204  call this%lak_linear_interpolation(i, this%tabstage(ifirst:ilast), &
2205  this%tabvolume(ifirst:ilast), &
2206  stage, volume)
2207  end if
2208  else
2209  do i = this%idxlakeconn(ilak), this%idxlakeconn(ilak+1)-1
2210  topl = this%telev(i)
2211  botl = this%belev(i)
2212  sat = squadraticsaturation(topl, botl, stage)
2213  sa = sat * this%sarea(i)
2214  if (stage < botl) then
2215  v = dzero
2216  else if (stage > botl .and. stage < topl) then
2217  v = sa * (stage - botl)
2218  else
2219  v = sa * (topl - botl) + sa * (stage - topl)
2220  end if
2221  volume = volume + v
2222  end do
2223  end if
2224  !
2225  ! -- return
2226  return
2227  end subroutine lak_calculate_vol

2298  subroutine lak_calculate_conn_conductance(this, ilak, iconn, stage, head, cond)
2299 ! ******************************************************************************
2300 ! lak_calculate_conn_conductance -- Calculate the conductance for a lake
2301 ! connection at a provided stage
2302 ! and groundwater head.
2303 ! ******************************************************************************
2304 !
2305 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
2306 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2307  ! -- dummy
2308  class(laktype),intent(inout) :: this
2309  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: ilak
2310  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: iconn
2311  real(DP), intent(in) :: stage
2312  real(DP), intent(in) :: head
2313  real(DP), intent(inout) :: cond
2314  ! -- local
2315  integer(I4B) :: node
2316  !real(DP) :: ss
2317  !real(DP) :: hh
2318  real(DP) :: vv
2319  real(DP) :: topl
2320  real(DP) :: botl
2321  real(DP) :: sat
2322  real(DP) :: wa
2323  ! -- formats
2324 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2325  cond = dzero
2326  topl = this%telev(iconn)
2327  botl = this%belev(iconn)
2328  call this%lak_calculate_cond_head(iconn, stage, head, vv)
2329  sat = squadraticsaturation(topl, botl, vv)
2330  ! vertical connection
2331  ! use full saturated conductance if top and bottom of the lake connection
2332  ! are equal
2333  if (this%ictype(iconn) == 0) then
2334  if (abs(topl-botl) < dprec) then
2335  sat = done
2336  end if
2337  ! horizontal connection
2338  ! use full saturated conductance if the connected cell is not convertible
2339  else if (this%ictype(iconn) == 1) then
2340  node = this%cellid(iconn)
2341  if (this%icelltype(node) == 0) then
2342  sat = done
2343  end if
2344  ! embedded connection
2345  else if (this%ictype(iconn) == 2 .or. this%ictype(iconn) == 3) then
2346  node = this%cellid(iconn)
2347  if (this%icelltype(node) == 0) then
2348  vv = this%telev(iconn)
2349  call this%lak_calculate_conn_warea(ilak, iconn, vv, vv, wa)
2350  else
2351  call this%lak_calculate_conn_warea(ilak, iconn, stage, head, wa)
2352  end if
2353  sat = wa
2354  end if
2355  cond = sat * this%satcond(iconn)
2356  !
2357  ! -- return
2358  return
2359  end subroutine lak_calculate_conn_conductance

2395  subroutine lak_calculate_conn_exchange(this, ilak, iconn, stage, head, flow, &
2396  gwfhcof, gwfrhs)
2397 ! ******************************************************************************
2398 ! lak_calculate_conn_exchange -- Calculate the groundwater-lake flow at a
2399 ! provided stage and groundwater head.
2400 ! ******************************************************************************
2401 !
2402 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
2403 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2404  ! -- dummy
2405  class(laktype),intent(inout) :: this
2406  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: ilak
2407  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: iconn
2408  real(DP), intent(in) :: stage
2409  real(DP), intent(in) :: head
2410  real(DP), intent(inout) :: flow
2411  real(DP), intent(inout), optional :: gwfhcof
2412  real(DP), intent(inout), optional :: gwfrhs
2413  ! -- local
2414  real(DP) :: botl
2415  real(DP) :: cond
2416  real(DP) :: ss
2417  real(DP) :: hh
2418  real(DP) :: gwfhcof0
2419  real(DP) :: gwfrhs0
2420  ! -- formats
2421 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2422  flow = dzero
2423  call this%lak_calculate_conn_conductance(ilak, iconn, stage, head, cond)
2424  botl = this%belev(iconn)
2425  !
2426  ! -- Set ss to stage or botl
2427  if (stage >= botl) then
2428  ss = stage
2429  else
2430  ss = botl
2431  end if
2432  !
2433  ! -- set hh to head or botl
2434  if (head >= botl) then
2435  hh = head
2436  else
2437  hh = botl
2438  end if
2439  !
2440  ! -- calculate flow, positive into lake
2441  flow = cond * (hh - ss)
2442  !
2443  ! -- Calculate gwfhcof and gwfrhs
2444  if (head >= botl) then
2445  gwfhcof0 = -cond
2446  gwfrhs0 = -cond * ss
2447  else
2448  gwfhcof0 = dzero
2449  gwfrhs0 = flow
2450  endif
2451  !
2452  ! Add density contributions, if active
2453  if (this%idense /= 0) then
2454  call this%lak_calculate_density_exchange(iconn, stage, head, cond, botl, &
2455  flow, gwfhcof0, gwfrhs0)
2456  end if
2457  !
2458  ! -- If present update gwfhcof and gwfrhs
2459  if (present(gwfhcof)) gwfhcof = gwfhcof0
2460  if (present(gwfrhs)) gwfrhs = gwfrhs0
2461  !
2462  ! -- return
2463  return
2464  end subroutine lak_calculate_conn_exchange

2738  subroutine lak_calculate_outlet_outflow(this, ilak, stage, avail, outoutf)
2739 ! ******************************************************************************
2740 ! lak_calculate_outlet_outflow -- Calculate the outlet outflow from a lake.
2741 ! ******************************************************************************
2742 !
2743 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
2744 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2745  ! -- dummy
2746  class(laktype),intent(inout) :: this
2747  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: ilak
2748  real(DP), intent(in) :: stage
2749  real(DP), intent(inout) :: avail
2750  real(DP), intent(inout) :: outoutf
2751  ! -- local
2752  integer(I4B) :: n
2753  real(DP) :: g
2754  real(DP) :: d
2755  real(DP) :: c
2756  real(DP) :: gsm
2757  real(DP) :: rate
2758  ! -- formats
2759 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2760  !
2761  outoutf = dzero
2762  do n = 1, this%noutlets
2763  if (this%lakein(n) == ilak) then
2764  rate = dzero
2765  d = stage - this%outinvert(n)
2766  if (this%outdmax > dzero) then
2767  if (d > this%outdmax) d = this%outdmax
2768  end if
2769  g = dgravity * this%convlength * this%convtime * this%convtime
2770  select case (this%iouttype(n))
2771  ! specified rate
2772  case(0)
2773  rate = this%outrate(n)
2774  if (-rate > avail) then
2775  rate = -avail
2776  end if
2777  ! manning
2778  case (1)
2779  if (d > dzero) then
2780  c = (this%convlength**donethird) * this%convtime
2781  gsm = dzero
2782  if (this%outrough(n) > dzero) then
2783  gsm = done / this%outrough(n)
2784  end if
2785  rate = -c * gsm * this%outwidth(n) * ( d**dfivethirds ) * &
2786  sqrt(this%outslope(n))
2787  end if
2788  ! weir
2789  case (2)
2790  if (d > dzero) then
2791  rate = -dtwothirds * dcd * this%outwidth(n) * d * &
2792  sqrt(dtwo * g * d)
2793  end if
2794  end select
2795  this%simoutrate(n) = rate
2796  avail = avail + rate
2797  outoutf = outoutf + rate
2798  end if
2799  end do
2800  !
2801  ! -- return
2802  return
2803  end subroutine lak_calculate_outlet_outflow

2976  subroutine lak_vol2stage(this, ilak, vol, stage)
2977 ! ******************************************************************************
2978 ! lak_vol2stage-- Determine the stage from a provided volume.
2979 ! ******************************************************************************
2980 !
2981 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
2982 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2983  ! -- dummy
2984  class(laktype),intent(inout) :: this
2985  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: ilak
2986  real(DP), intent(in) :: vol
2987  real(DP), intent(inout) :: stage
2988  ! -- local
2989  integer(I4B) :: i
2990  integer(I4B) :: ibs
2991  real(DP) :: s0, s1, sm
2992  real(DP) :: v0, v1, vm
2993  real(DP) :: f0, f1, fm
2994  real(DP) :: sa
2995  real(DP) :: en0, en1
2996  real(DP) :: ds, ds0
2997  real(DP) :: denom
2998  ! -- formats
2999 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3000  s0 = this%lakebot(ilak)
3001  call this%lak_calculate_vol(ilak, s0, v0)
3002  s1 = this%laketop(ilak)
3003  call this%lak_calculate_vol(ilak, s1, v1)
3004  ! -- zero volume
3005  if (vol <= v0) then
3006  stage = s0
3007  ! -- linear relation between stage and volume above top of lake
3008  else if (vol >= v1) then
3009  call this%lak_calculate_sarea(ilak, s1, sa)
3010  stage = s1 + (vol - v1) / sa
3011  ! -- use combination of secant and bisection
3012  else
3013  en0 = s0
3014  en1 = s1
3015  ! sm = s1 ! causes divide by zero in 1st line in secantbisection loop
3016  ! sm = s0 ! causes divide by zero in 1st line in secantbisection loop
3017  sm = dzero
3018  f0 = vol - v0
3019  f1 = vol - v1
3020  ibs = 0
3021  secantbisection: do i = 1, 150
3022  denom = f1 - f0
3023  if (denom /= dzero) then
3024  ds = f1 * (s1 - s0) / denom
3025  else
3026  ibs = 13
3027  end if
3028  if (i == 1) then
3029  ds0 = ds
3030  end if
3031  ! -- use bisection if end points are exceeded
3032  if (sm < en0 .or. sm > en1) ibs = 13
3033  ! -- use bisection if secant method stagnates or if
3034  ! ds exceeds previous ds - bisection would occur
3035  ! after conditions exceeded in 13 iterations
3036  if (ds*ds0 < dprec .or. abs(ds) > abs(ds0)) ibs = ibs + 1
3037  if (ibs > 12) then
3038  ds = dhalf * (s1 - s0)
3039  ibs = 0
3040  end if
3041  sm = s1 - ds
3042  if (abs(ds) < dem6) then
3043  exit secantbisection
3044  end if
3045  call this%lak_calculate_vol(ilak, sm, vm)
3046  fm = vol - vm
3047  s0 = s1
3048  f0 = f1
3049  s1 = sm
3050  f1 = fm
3051  ds0 = ds
3052  end do secantbisection
3053  stage = sm
3054  if (abs(ds) >= dem6) then
3055  write(this%iout, '(1x,a,1x,i5,4(1x,a,1x,g15.6))') &
3056  & 'LAK_VOL2STAGE failed for lake', ilak, 'volume error =', fm, &
3057  & 'finding stage (', stage, ') for volume =', vol, &
3058  & 'final change in stage =', ds
3059  end if
3060  end if
3061  !
3062  ! -- return
3063  return
3064  end subroutine lak_vol2stage

3602  else

3689  subroutine lak_ad(this)
3690 ! ******************************************************************************
3691 ! lak_ad -- Add package connection to matrix
3692 ! ******************************************************************************
3693 !
3694 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
3695 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3696  ! -- modules
3697  use simvariablesmodule, only: ifailedstepretry
3698  ! -- dummy
3699  class(laktype) :: this
3700  ! -- local
3701  integer(I4B) :: n
3702  integer(I4B) :: j
3703  integer(I4B) :: iaux
3704 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3705  !
3706  ! -- Advance the time series
3707  call this%TsManager%ad()
3708  !
3709  ! -- update auxiliary variables by copying from the derived-type time
3710  ! series variable into the bndpackage auxvar variable so that this
3711  ! information is properly written to the GWF budget file
3712  if (this%naux > 0) then
3713  do n = 1, this%nlakes
3714  do j = this%idxlakeconn(n), this%idxlakeconn(n + 1) - 1
3715  do iaux = 1, this%naux
3716  if (this%noupdateauxvar(iaux) /= 0) cycle
3717  this%auxvar(iaux, j) = this%lauxvar(iaux, n)
3718  end do
3719  end do
3720  end do
3721  end if
3722  !
3723  ! -- Update or restore state
3724  if (ifailedstepretry == 0) then
3725  !
3726  ! -- copy xnew into xold and set xnewpak to stage for
3727  ! constant stage lakes
3728  do n = 1, this%nlakes
3729  this%xoldpak(n) = this%xnewpak(n)
3730  this%stageiter(n) = this%xnewpak(n)
3731  if (this%iboundpak(n) < 0) then
3732  this%xnewpak(n) = this%stage(n)
3733  end if
3734  this%seep0(n) = dzero
3735  end do
3736  else
3737  !
3738  ! -- copy xold back into xnew as this is a
3739  ! retry of this time step
3740  do n = 1, this%nlakes
3741  this%xnewpak(n) = this%xoldpak(n)
3742  this%stageiter(n) = this%xnewpak(n)
3743  if (this%iboundpak(n) < 0) then
3744  this%xnewpak(n) = this%stage(n)
3745  end if
3746  this%seep0(n) = dzero
3747  end do
3748  end if
3749  !
3750  ! -- pakmvrobj ad
3751  if (this%imover == 1) then
3752  call this%pakmvrobj%ad()
3753  end if
3754  !
3755  ! -- For each observation, push simulated value and corresponding
3756  ! simulation time from "current" to "preceding" and reset
3757  ! "current" value.
3758  call this%obs%obs_ad()
3759  !
3760  ! -- return
3761  return
3762  end subroutine lak_ad

3764  subroutine lak_cf(this, reset_mover)
3765  ! ******************************************************************************
3766  ! lak_cf -- Formulate the HCOF and RHS terms
3767  ! Subroutine: (1) skip if no lakes
3768  ! (2) calculate hcof and rhs
3769  ! ******************************************************************************
3770  !
3771  ! SPECIFICATIONS:
3772  ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3773  ! -- dummy
3774  class(laktype) :: this
3775  logical, intent(in), optional :: reset_mover
3776  ! -- local
3777  integer(I4B) :: j, n
3778  integer(I4B) :: igwfnode
3779  real(DP) :: hlak, blak
3780  logical :: lrm
3781  ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3782  !!
3783  !! -- Calculate lak conductance and update package RHS and HCOF
3784  !call this%lak_cfupdate()
3785  !
3786  ! -- save groundwater seepage for lake solution
3787  do n = 1, this%nlakes
3788  this%seep0(n) = this%seep(n)
3789  end do
3790  !
3791  ! -- save variables for convergence check
3792  do n = 1, this%nlakes
3793  this%s0(n) = this%xnewpak(n)
3794  call this%lak_calculate_exchange(n, this%s0(n), this%qgwf0(n))
3795  end do
3796  !
3797  ! -- pakmvrobj cf
3798  lrm = .true.
3799  if (present(reset_mover)) lrm = reset_mover
3800  if(this%imover == 1 .and. lrm) then
3801  call this%pakmvrobj%cf()
3802  end if
3803  !
3804  ! -- find highest active cell
3805  do n = 1, this%nlakes
3806  do j = this%idxlakeconn(n), this%idxlakeconn(n+1)-1
3807  ! -- skip horizontal connections
3808  if (this%ictype(j) /= 0) then
3809  cycle
3810  end if
3811  igwfnode = this%nodesontop(j)
3812  if (this%ibound(igwfnode) == 0) then
3813  call this%dis%highest_active(igwfnode, this%ibound)
3814  end if
3815  this%nodelist(j) = igwfnode
3816  this%cellid(j) = igwfnode
3817  end do
3818  end do
3819  !
3820  ! -- reset ibound for cells where lake stage is above the bottom
3821  ! of the lake in the cell or the lake is inactive - only applied to
3822  ! vertical connections
3823  do n = 1, this%nlakes
3824  !
3825  hlak = this%xnewpak(n)
3826  !
3827  ! -- Go through lake connections
3828  do j = this%idxlakeconn(n), this%idxlakeconn(n+1)-1
3829  !
3830  ! -- assign gwf node number
3831  igwfnode = this%cellid(j)
3832  !
3833  ! -- skip inactive or constant head GWF cells
3834  if (this%ibound(igwfnode) < 1) then
3835  cycle
3836  end if
3837  !
3838  ! -- skip horizontal connections
3839  if (this%ictype(j) /= 0) then
3840  cycle
3841  end if
3842  !
3843  ! -- skip embedded lakes
3844  if (this%ictype(j) == 2 .or. this%ictype(j) == 3) then
3845  cycle
3846  end if
3847  !
3848  ! -- Mark ibound for dry lakes; reset to 1 otherwise
3849  blak = this%belev(j)
3850  if (hlak > blak .or. this%iboundpak(n) == 0) then
3851  this%ibound(igwfnode) = 10000
3852  else
3853  this%ibound(igwfnode) = 1
3854  end if
3855  end do
3856 
3857  end do
3858  !
3859  ! -- Store the lake stage and cond in bound array for other
3860  ! packages, such as the BUY package
3861  call this%lak_bound_update()
3862  !
3863  ! -- Return
3864  return
3865  end subroutine lak_cf
