3867  subroutine lak_fc(this, rhs, ia, idxglo, amatsln)
3868  ! **************************************************************************
3869  ! lak_fc -- Copy rhs and hcof into solution rhs and amat
3870  ! **************************************************************************
3871  !
3872  ! SPECIFICATIONS:
3873  ! --------------------------------------------------------------------------
3874  ! -- dummy
3875  class(laktype) :: this
3876  real(DP), dimension(:), intent(inout) :: rhs
3877  integer(I4B), dimension(:), intent(in) :: ia
3878  integer(I4B), dimension(:), intent(in) :: idxglo
3879  real(DP), dimension(:), intent(inout) :: amatsln
3880  ! -- local
3881  integer(I4B) :: j, n
3882  integer(I4B) :: igwfnode
3883  integer(I4B) :: ipossymd
3884 ! --------------------------------------------------------------------------
3885  !
3886  ! -- pakmvrobj fc
3887  if(this%imover == 1) then
3888  call this%pakmvrobj%fc()
3889  end if
3890  !
3891  ! -- make a stab at a solution
3892  call this%lak_solve()
3893  !
3894  ! -- add terms to the gwf matrix
3895  do n = 1, this%nlakes
3896  do j = this%idxlakeconn(n), this%idxlakeconn(n+1)-1
3897  igwfnode = this%cellid(j)
3898  if (this%ibound(igwfnode) < 1) cycle
3899  ipossymd = idxglo(ia(igwfnode))
3900  amatsln(ipossymd) = amatsln(ipossymd) + this%hcof(j)
3901  rhs(igwfnode) = rhs(igwfnode) + this%rhs(j)
3902  end do
3903  end do
3904  !
3905  ! -- return
3906  return
3907  end subroutine lak_fc
3908 
3909  subroutine lak_fn(this, rhs, ia, idxglo, amatsln)
3910 ! **************************************************************************
3911 ! lak_fn -- Fill newton terms
3912 ! **************************************************************************
3913 !
3914 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
3915 ! --------------------------------------------------------------------------
3916  ! -- dummy
3917  class(laktype) :: this
3918  real(DP), dimension(:), intent(inout) :: rhs
3919  integer(I4B), dimension(:), intent(in) :: ia
3920  integer(I4B), dimension(:), intent(in) :: idxglo
3921  real(DP), dimension(:), intent(inout) :: amatsln
3922  ! -- local
3923  integer(I4B) :: j, n
3924  integer(I4B) :: ipos
3925  integer(I4B) :: igwfnode
3926  integer(I4B) :: idry
3927  real(DP) :: hlak
3928  real(DP) :: avail
3929  real(DP) :: ra
3930  real(DP) :: ro
3931  real(DP) :: qinf
3932  real(DP) :: ex
3933  real(DP) :: head
3934  real(DP) :: q
3935  real(DP) :: q1
3936  real(DP) :: rterm
3937  real(DP) :: drterm
3938 ! --------------------------------------------------------------------------
3939  do n = 1, this%nlakes
3940  if (this%iboundpak(n) == 0) cycle
3941  hlak = this%xnewpak(n)
3942  call this%lak_calculate_available(n, hlak, avail, &
3943  ra, ro, qinf, ex, this%delh)
3944  do j = this%idxlakeconn(n), this%idxlakeconn(n+1)-1
3945  igwfnode = this%cellid(j)
3946  ipos = ia(igwfnode)
3947  head = this%xnew(igwfnode)
3948  if (-this%hcof(j) > dzero) then
3949  if (this%ibound(igwfnode) > 0) then
3950  ! -- estimate lake-aquifer exchange with perturbed groundwater head
3951  ! exchange is relative to the lake
3952  !avail = DEP20
3953  call this%lak_estimate_conn_exchange(2, n, j, idry, hlak, head+this%delh, q1, avail)
3954  q1 = -q1
3955  ! -- calculate unperturbed lake-aquifer exchange
3956  q = this%hcof(j) * head - this%rhs(j)
3957  ! -- calculate rterm
3958  rterm = this%hcof(j) * head
3959  ! -- calculate derivative
3960  drterm = (q1 - q) / this%delh
3961  ! -- add terms to convert conductance formulation into
3962  ! newton-raphson formulation
3963  amatsln(idxglo(ipos)) = amatsln(idxglo(ipos)) + drterm - this%hcof(j)
3964  rhs(igwfnode) = rhs(igwfnode) - rterm + drterm * head
3965  end if
3966  end if
3967  end do
3968  end do
3969 
3970  !
3971  ! -- return
3972  return
3973  end subroutine lak_fn
3974 
3975  subroutine lak_cc(this, innertot, kiter, iend, icnvgmod, cpak, ipak, dpak)
3976 ! **************************************************************************
3977 ! lak_cc -- Final convergence check for package
3978 ! **************************************************************************
3979 !
3980 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
3981 ! --------------------------------------------------------------------------
3982  use tdismodule, only: totim, kstp, kper, delt
3983  ! -- dummy
3984  class(laktype), intent(inout) :: this
3985  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: innertot
3986  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: kiter
3987  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: iend
3988  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: icnvgmod
3989  character(len=LENPAKLOC), intent(inout) :: cpak
3990  integer(I4B), intent(inout) :: ipak
3991  real(DP), intent(inout) :: dpak
3992  ! -- local
3993  character(len=LENPAKLOC) :: cloc
3994  character(len=LINELENGTH) :: tag
3995  integer(I4B) :: icheck
3996  integer(I4B) :: ipakfail
3997  integer(I4B) :: locdhmax
3998  integer(I4B) :: locdgwfmax
3999  integer(I4B) :: locdqoutmax
4000  integer(I4B) :: ntabrows
4001  integer(I4B) :: ntabcols
4002  integer(I4B) :: n
4003  real(DP) :: area
4004  real(DP) :: gwf0
4005  real(DP) :: gwf
4006  real(DP) :: dh
4007  real(DP) :: dgwf
4008  real(DP) :: hlak0
4009  real(DP) :: hlak
4010  real(DP) :: qout0
4011  real(DP) :: qout
4012  real(DP) :: dqout
4013  real(DP) :: inf
4014  real(DP) :: ra
4015  real(DP) :: ro
4016  real(DP) :: qinf
4017  real(DP) :: ex
4018  real(DP) :: dhmax
4019  real(DP) :: dgwfmax
4020  real(DP) :: dqoutmax
4021  ! format
4022 ! --------------------------------------------------------------------------
4023  !
4024  ! -- initialize local variables
4025  icheck = this%iconvchk
4026  ipakfail = 0
4027  locdhmax = 0
4028  locdgwfmax = 0
4029  locdqoutmax = 0
4030  dhmax = dzero
4031  dgwfmax = dzero
4032  dqoutmax = dzero
4033  !
4034  ! -- if not saving package convergence data on check convergence if
4035  ! the model is considered converged
4036  if (this%ipakcsv == 0) then
4037  if (icnvgmod == 0) then
4038  icheck = 0
4039  end if
4040  !
4041  ! -- saving package convergence data
4042  else
4043  !
4044  ! -- header for package csv
4045  if (.not. associated(this%pakcsvtab)) then
4046  !
4047  ! -- determine the number of columns and rows
4048  ntabrows = 1
4049  ntabcols = 9
4050  if (this%noutlets > 0) then
4051  ntabcols = ntabcols + 2
4052  end if
4053  !
4054  ! -- setup table
4055  call table_cr(this%pakcsvtab, this%packName, '')
4056  call this%pakcsvtab%table_df(ntabrows, ntabcols, this%ipakcsv, &
4057  lineseparator=.false., separator=',', &
4058  finalize=.false.)
4059  !
4060  ! -- add columns to package csv
4061  tag = 'total_inner_iterations'
4062  call this%pakcsvtab%initialize_column(tag, 10, alignment=tableft)
4063  tag = 'totim'
4064  call this%pakcsvtab%initialize_column(tag, 10, alignment=tableft)
4065  tag = 'kper'
4066  call this%pakcsvtab%initialize_column(tag, 10, alignment=tableft)
4067  tag = 'kstp'
4068  call this%pakcsvtab%initialize_column(tag, 10, alignment=tableft)
4069  tag = 'nouter'
4070  call this%pakcsvtab%initialize_column(tag, 10, alignment=tableft)
4071  tag = 'dvmax'
4072  call this%pakcsvtab%initialize_column(tag, 15, alignment=tableft)
4073  tag = 'dvmax_loc'
4074  call this%pakcsvtab%initialize_column(tag, 15, alignment=tableft)
4075  tag = 'dgwfmax'
4076  call this%pakcsvtab%initialize_column(tag, 15, alignment=tableft)
4077  tag = 'dgwfmax_loc'
4078  call this%pakcsvtab%initialize_column(tag, 15, alignment=tableft)
4079  if (this%noutlets > 0) then
4080  tag = 'dqoutmax'
4081  call this%pakcsvtab%initialize_column(tag, 15, alignment=tableft)
4082  tag = 'dqoutmax_loc'
4083  call this%pakcsvtab%initialize_column(tag, 15, alignment=tableft)
4084  end if
4085  end if
4086  end if
4087  !
4088  ! -- perform package convergence check
4089  if (icheck /= 0) then
4090  final_check: do n = 1, this%nlakes
4091  if (this%iboundpak(n) < 1) cycle
4092  !
4093  ! -- set previous and current lake stage
4094  hlak0 = this%s0(n)
4095  hlak = this%xnewpak(n)
4096  !
4097  ! -- stage difference
4098  dh = hlak0 - hlak
4099  !
4100  ! -- calculate surface area
4101  call this%lak_calculate_sarea(n, hlak, area)
4102  !
4103  ! -- change in gwf exchange
4104  dgwf = dzero
4105  if (area > dzero) then
4106  gwf0 = this%qgwf0(n)
4107  call this%lak_calculate_exchange(n, hlak, gwf)
4108  dgwf = (gwf0 - gwf) * delt / area
4109  end if
4110  !
4111  ! -- change in outflows
4112  dqout = dzero
4113  if (this%noutlets > 0) then
4114  if (area > dzero) then
4115  call this%lak_calculate_available(n, hlak0, inf, ra, ro, qinf, ex)
4116  call this%lak_calculate_outlet_outflow(n, hlak0, inf, qout0)
4117  call this%lak_calculate_available(n, hlak, inf, ra, ro, qinf, ex)
4118  call this%lak_calculate_outlet_outflow(n, hlak, inf, qout)
4119  dqout = (qout0 - qout) * delt / area
4120  end if
4121  end if
4122  !
4123  ! -- evaluate magnitude of differences
4124  if (n == 1) then
4125  locdhmax = n
4126  dhmax = dh
4127  locdgwfmax = n
4128  dgwfmax = dgwf
4129  locdqoutmax = n
4130  dqoutmax = dqout
4131  else
4132  if (abs(dh) > abs(dhmax)) then
4133  locdhmax = n
4134  dhmax = dh
4135  end if
4136  if (abs(dgwf) > abs(dgwfmax)) then
4137  locdgwfmax = n
4138  dgwfmax = dgwf
4139  end if
4140  if (abs(dqout) > abs(dqoutmax)) then
4141  locdqoutmax = n
4142  dqoutmax = dqout
4143  end if
4144  end if
4145  end do final_check
4146  !
4147  ! -- set dpak and cpak
4148  if (abs(dhmax) > abs(dpak)) then
4149  ipak = locdhmax
4150  dpak = dhmax
4151  write(cloc, "(a,'-',a)") &
4152  trim(this%packName), 'stage'
4153  cpak = trim(cloc)
4154  end if
4155  if (abs(dgwfmax) > abs(dpak)) then
4156  ipak = locdgwfmax
4157  dpak = dgwfmax
4158  write(cloc, "(a,'-',a)") &
4159  trim(this%packName), 'gwf'
4160  cpak = trim(cloc)
4161  end if
4162  if (this%noutlets > 0) then
4163  if (abs(dqoutmax) > abs(dpak)) then
4164  ipak = locdqoutmax
4165  dpak = dqoutmax
4166  write(cloc, "(a,'-',a)") &
4167  trim(this%packName), 'outlet'
4168  cpak = trim(cloc)
4169  end if
4170  end if
4171  !
4172  ! -- write convergence data to package csv
4173  if (this%ipakcsv /= 0) then
4174  !
4175  ! -- write the data
4176  call this%pakcsvtab%add_term(innertot)
4177  call this%pakcsvtab%add_term(totim)
4178  call this%pakcsvtab%add_term(kper)
4179  call this%pakcsvtab%add_term(kstp)
4180  call this%pakcsvtab%add_term(kiter)
4181  call this%pakcsvtab%add_term(dhmax)
4182  call this%pakcsvtab%add_term(locdhmax)
4183  call this%pakcsvtab%add_term(dgwfmax)
4184  call this%pakcsvtab%add_term(locdgwfmax)
4185  if (this%noutlets > 0) then
4186  call this%pakcsvtab%add_term(dqoutmax)
4187  call this%pakcsvtab%add_term(locdqoutmax)
4188  end if
4189  !
4190  ! -- finalize the package csv
4191  if (iend == 1) then
4192  call this%pakcsvtab%finalize_table()
4193  end if
4194  end if
4195  end if
4196  !
4197  ! -- return
4198  return
4199  end subroutine lak_cc
4200 
4201  subroutine lak_cq(this, x, flowja, iadv)
4202 ! ******************************************************************************
4203 ! lak_cq -- Calculate flows
4204 ! ******************************************************************************
4205 !
4206 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
4207 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4208  ! -- modules
4209  use tdismodule, only: delt
4210  ! -- dummy
4211  class(laktype), intent(inout) :: this
4212  real(DP), dimension(:), intent(in) :: x
4213  real(DP), dimension(:), contiguous, intent(inout) :: flowja
4214  integer(I4B), optional, intent(in) :: iadv
4215  ! -- local
4216  real(DP) :: rrate
4217  real(DP) :: chratin, chratout
4218  ! -- for budget
4219  integer(I4B) :: j, n
4220  real(DP) :: hlak
4221  real(DP) :: v0, v1
4222 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4223  !
4224  call this%lak_solve(update=.false.)
4225  !
4226  ! -- call base functionality in bnd_cq. This will calculate lake-gwf flows
4227  ! and put them into this%simvals
4228  call this%BndType%bnd_cq(x, flowja, iadv=1)
4229  !
4230  ! -- calculate several budget terms
4231  chratin = dzero
4232  chratout = dzero
4233  do n = 1, this%nlakes
4234  this%chterm(n) = dzero
4235  if (this%iboundpak(n) == 0) cycle
4236  hlak = this%xnewpak(n)
4237  call this%lak_calculate_vol(n, hlak, v1)
4238  !
4239  ! -- add budget terms for active lakes
4240  if (this%iboundpak(n) /= 0) then
4241  !
4242  ! -- rainfall
4243  rrate = this%precip(n)
4244  call this%lak_accumulate_chterm(n, rrate, chratin, chratout)
4245  !
4246  ! -- evaporation
4247  rrate = this%evap(n)
4248  call this%lak_accumulate_chterm(n, rrate, chratin, chratout)
4249  !
4250  ! -- runoff
4251  rrate = this%runoff(n)
4252  call this%lak_accumulate_chterm(n, rrate, chratin, chratout)
4253  !
4254  ! -- inflow
4255  rrate = this%inflow(n)
4256  call this%lak_accumulate_chterm(n, rrate, chratin, chratout)
4257  !
4258  ! -- withdrawals
4259  rrate = this%withr(n)
4260  call this%lak_accumulate_chterm(n, rrate, chratin, chratout)
4261  !
4262  ! -- add lake storage changes
4263  rrate = dzero
4264  if (this%iboundpak(n) > 0) then
4265  if (this%gwfiss /= 1) then
4266  call this%lak_calculate_vol(n, this%xoldpak(n), v0)
4267  rrate = -(v1 - v0) / delt
4268  call this%lak_accumulate_chterm(n, rrate, chratin, chratout)
4269  end if
4270  end if
4271  this%qsto(n) = rrate
4272  !
4273  ! -- add external outlets
4274  call this%lak_get_external_outlet(n, rrate)
4275  call this%lak_accumulate_chterm(n, rrate, chratin, chratout)
4276  !
4277  ! -- add mover terms
4278  if (this%imover == 1) then
4279  if (this%iboundpak(n) /= 0) then
4280  rrate = this%pakmvrobj%get_qfrommvr(n)
4281  else
4282  rrate = dzero
4283  end if
4284  call this%lak_accumulate_chterm(n, rrate, chratin, chratout)
4285  endif
4286  end if
4287  end do
4288  !
4289  ! -- gwf flow and constant flow to lake
4290  do n = 1, this%nlakes
4291  if (this%iboundpak(n) == 0) cycle
4292  rrate = dzero
4293  do j = this%idxlakeconn(n), this%idxlakeconn(n+1)-1
4294  rrate = this%simvals(j)
4295  this%qleak(j) = -rrate
4296  call this%lak_accumulate_chterm(n, rrate, chratin, chratout)
4297  end do
4298  end do
4299  !
4300  ! -- fill the budget object
4301  call this%lak_fill_budobj()
4302  !
4303  ! -- return
4304  return
4305  end subroutine lak_cq

4362  ibinun = this%istageout
4363  end if

4392  call this%lak_calculate_warea(n, stage, wa)
4393  call this%lak_calculate_vol(n, stage, v)
4394  if(this%inamedbound==1) then
4395  call this%stagetab%add_term(this%lakename(n))
4396  end if
4397  call this%stagetab%add_term(n)
4398  call this%stagetab%add_term(stage)
4399  call this%stagetab%add_term(sa)
4400  call this%stagetab%add_term(wa)
4401  call this%stagetab%add_term(v)
4402  end do
4403  end if

4792  subroutine lak_bd_obs(this)
4793  ! **************************************************************************
4794  ! lak_bd_obs
4795  ! -- Calculate observations this time step and call
4796  ! ObsType%SaveOneSimval for each LakType observation.
4797  ! **************************************************************************
4798  !
4799  ! SPECIFICATIONS:
4800  ! --------------------------------------------------------------------------
4801  ! -- dummy
4802  class(laktype) :: this
4803  ! -- local
4804  integer(I4B) :: i
4805  integer(I4B) :: igwfnode
4806  integer(I4B) :: j
4807  integer(I4B) :: jj
4808  integer(I4B) :: n
4809  real(DP) :: hgwf
4810  real(DP) :: hlak
4811  real(DP) :: v
4812  real(DP) :: v2
4813  type(observetype), pointer :: obsrv => null()
4814  !---------------------------------------------------------------------------
4815  !
4816  ! Write simulated values for all LAK observations
4817  if (this%obs%npakobs > 0) then
4818  call this%obs%obs_bd_clear()
4819  do i = 1, this%obs%npakobs
4820  obsrv => this%obs%pakobs(i)%obsrv
4821  do j = 1, obsrv%indxbnds_count
4822  v = dnodata
4823  jj = obsrv%indxbnds(j)
4824  select case (obsrv%ObsTypeId)
4825  case ('STAGE')
4826  if (this%iboundpak(jj) /= 0) then
4827  v = this%xnewpak(jj)
4828  end if
4829  case ('EXT-INFLOW')
4830  if (this%iboundpak(jj) /= 0) then
4831  call this%lak_calculate_inflow(jj, v)
4832  end if
4833  case ('OUTLET-INFLOW')
4834  if (this%iboundpak(jj) /= 0) then
4835  call this%lak_calculate_outlet_inflow(jj, v)
4836  end if
4837  case ('INFLOW')
4838  if (this%iboundpak(jj) /= 0) then
4839  call this%lak_calculate_inflow(jj, v)
4840  call this%lak_calculate_outlet_inflow(jj, v2)
4841  v = v + v2
4842  end if
4843  case ('FROM-MVR')
4844  if (this%iboundpak(jj) /= 0) then
4845  if (this%imover == 1) then
4846  v = this%pakmvrobj%get_qfrommvr(jj)
4847  end if
4848  end if
4849  case ('RAINFALL')
4850  if (this%iboundpak(jj) /= 0) then
4851  v = this%precip(jj)
4852  end if
4853  case ('RUNOFF')
4854  if (this%iboundpak(jj) /= 0) then
4855  v = this%runoff(jj)
4856  end if
4857  case ('LAK')
4858  n = this%imap(jj)
4859  if (this%iboundpak(n) /= 0) then
4860  igwfnode = this%cellid(jj)
4861  hgwf = this%xnew(igwfnode)
4862  if (this%hcof(jj) /= dzero) then
4863  v = -(this%hcof(jj) * (this%xnewpak(n) - hgwf))
4864  else
4865  v = -this%rhs(jj)
4866  end if
4867  end if
4868  case ('EVAPORATION')
4869  if (this%iboundpak(jj) /= 0) then
4870  v = this%evap(jj)
4871  end if
4872  case ('WITHDRAWAL')
4873  if (this%iboundpak(jj) /= 0) then
4874  v = this%withr(jj)
4875  end if
4876  case ('EXT-OUTFLOW')
4877  n = this%lakein(jj)
4878  if (this%iboundpak(n) /= 0) then
4879  if (this%lakeout(jj) == 0) then
4880  v = this%simoutrate(jj)
4881  if (v < dzero) then
4882  if (this%imover == 1) then
4883  v = v + this%pakmvrobj%get_qtomvr(jj)
4884  end if
4885  end if
4886  end if
4887  end if
4888  case ('TO-MVR')
4889  n = this%lakein(jj)
4890  if (this%iboundpak(n) /= 0) then
4891  if (this%imover == 1) then
4892  v = this%pakmvrobj%get_qtomvr(jj)
4893  if (v > dzero) then
4894  v = -v
4895  end if
4896  end if
4897  end if
4898  case ('STORAGE')
4899  if (this%iboundpak(jj) /= 0) then
4900  v = this%qsto(jj)
4901  end if
4902  case ('CONSTANT')
4903  if (this%iboundpak(jj) /= 0) then
4904  v = this%chterm(jj)
4905  end if
4906  case ('OUTLET')
4907  n = this%lakein(jj)
4908  if (this%iboundpak(jj) /= 0) then
4909  v = this%simoutrate(jj)
4910  !if (this%imover == 1) then
4911  ! v = v + this%pakmvrobj%get_qtomvr(jj)
4912  !end if
4913  end if
4914  case ('VOLUME')
4915  if (this%iboundpak(jj) /= 0) then
4916  call this%lak_calculate_vol(jj, this%xnewpak(jj), v)
4917  end if
4918  case ('SURFACE-AREA')
4919  if (this%iboundpak(jj) /= 0) then
4920  hlak = this%xnewpak(jj)
4921  call this%lak_calculate_sarea(jj, hlak, v)
4922  end if
4923  case ('WETTED-AREA')
4924  n = this%imap(jj)
4925  if (this%iboundpak(n) /= 0) then
4926  hlak = this%xnewpak(n)
4927  igwfnode = this%cellid(jj)
4928  hgwf = this%xnew(igwfnode)
4929  call this%lak_calculate_conn_warea(n, jj, hlak, hgwf, v)
4930  end if
4931  case ('CONDUCTANCE')
4932  n = this%imap(jj)
4933  if (this%iboundpak(n) /= 0) then
4934  hlak = this%xnewpak(n)
4935  igwfnode = this%cellid(jj)
4936  hgwf = this%xnew(igwfnode)
4937  call this%lak_calculate_conn_conductance(n, jj, hlak, hgwf, v)
4938  end if
4939  case default
4940  errmsg = 'Unrecognized observation type: ' // trim(obsrv%ObsTypeId)
4941  call store_error(errmsg)
4942  end select
4943  call this%obs%SaveOneSimval(obsrv, v)
4944  end do
4945  end do
4946  !
4947  ! -- write summary of error messages
4948  if (count_errors() > 0) then
4949  call store_error_unit(this%inunit)
4950  end if
4951  end if
4952  !
4953  return
4954  end subroutine lak_bd_obs

4957  subroutine lak_rp_obs(this)
4958  use tdismodule, only: kper
4959  ! -- dummy
4960  class(laktype), intent(inout) :: this
4961  ! -- local
4962  integer(I4B) :: i
4963  integer(I4B) :: j
4964  integer(I4B) :: nn1
4965  integer(I4B) :: nn2
4966  integer(I4B) :: jj
4967  character(len=LENBOUNDNAME) :: bname
4968  logical :: jfound
4969  class(observetype), pointer :: obsrv => null()
4970  ! --------------------------------------------------------------------------
4971  ! -- formats
4972 10 format('Boundary "',a,'" for observation "',a, &
4973  '" is invalid in package "',a,'"')
4974  !
4975  ! -- process each package observation
4976  ! only done the first stress period since boundaries are fixed
4977  ! for the simulation
4978  if (kper == 1) then
4979  do i = 1, this%obs%npakobs
4980  obsrv => this%obs%pakobs(i)%obsrv
4981  !
4982  ! -- get node number 1
4983  nn1 = obsrv%NodeNumber
4984  if (nn1 == namedboundflag) then
4985  bname = obsrv%FeatureName
4986  if (bname /= '') then
4987  ! -- Observation lake is based on a boundary name.
4988  ! Iterate through all lakes to identify and store
4989  ! corresponding index in bound array.
4990  jfound = .false.
4991  if (obsrv%ObsTypeId=='LAK' .or. &
4992  obsrv%ObsTypeId=='CONDUCTANCE' .or. &
4993  obsrv%ObsTypeId=='WETTED-AREA') then
4994  do j = 1, this%nlakes
4995  do jj = this%idxlakeconn(j), this%idxlakeconn(j+1) - 1
4996  if (this%boundname(jj) == bname) then
4997  jfound = .true.
4998  call obsrv%AddObsIndex(jj)
4999  end if
5000  end do
5001  end do
5002  else if (obsrv%ObsTypeId=='EXT-OUTFLOW' .or. &
5003  obsrv%ObsTypeId=='TO-MVR' .or. &
5004  obsrv%ObsTypeId=='OUTLET') then
5005  do j = 1, this%noutlets
5006  jj = this%lakein(j)
5007  if (this%lakename(jj) == bname) then
5008  jfound = .true.
5009  call obsrv%AddObsIndex(j)
5010  end if
5011  end do
5012  else
5013  do j = 1, this%nlakes
5014  if (this%lakename(j) == bname) then
5015  jfound = .true.
5016  call obsrv%AddObsIndex(j)
5017  end if
5018  end do
5019  end if
5020  if (.not. jfound) then
5021  write(errmsg,10)trim(bname), trim(obsrv%Name), trim(this%packName)
5022  call store_error(errmsg)
5023  end if
5024  end if
5025  else
5026  if (obsrv%indxbnds_count == 0) then
5027  if (obsrv%ObsTypeId=='LAK' .or. &
5028  obsrv%ObsTypeId=='CONDUCTANCE' .or. &
5029  obsrv%ObsTypeId=='WETTED-AREA') then
5030  nn2 = obsrv%NodeNumber2
5031  j = this%idxlakeconn(nn1) + nn2 - 1
5032  call obsrv%AddObsIndex(j)
5033  else
5034  call obsrv%AddObsIndex(nn1)
5035  end if
5036  else
5037  errmsg = 'Programming error in lak_rp_obs'
5038  call store_error(errmsg)
5039  endif
5040  end if
5041  !
5042  ! -- catch non-cumulative observation assigned to observation defined
5043  ! by a boundname that is assigned to more than one element
5044  if (obsrv%ObsTypeId == 'STAGE') then
5045  if (obsrv%indxbnds_count > 1) then
5046  write(errmsg, '(a,3(1x,a))') &
5047  trim(adjustl(obsrv%ObsTypeId)), &
5048  'for observation', trim(adjustl(obsrv%Name)), &
5049  ' must be assigned to a lake with a unique boundname.'
5050  call store_error(errmsg)
5051  end if
5052  end if
5053  !
5054  ! -- check that index values are valid
5055  if (obsrv%ObsTypeId=='TO-MVR' .or. &
5056  obsrv%ObsTypeId=='EXT-OUTFLOW' .or. &
5057  obsrv%ObsTypeId=='OUTLET') then
5058  do j = 1, obsrv%indxbnds_count
5059  nn1 = obsrv%indxbnds(j)
5060  if (nn1 < 1 .or. nn1 > this%noutlets) then
5061  write(errmsg, '(a,1x,a,1x,i0,1x,a,1x,i0,a)') &
5062  trim(adjustl(obsrv%ObsTypeId)), &
5063  ' outlet must be > 0 and <=', this%noutlets, &
5064  '(specified value is ', nn1, ')'
5065  call store_error(errmsg)
5066  end if
5067  end do
5068  else if (obsrv%ObsTypeId=='LAK' .or. &
5069  obsrv%ObsTypeId=='CONDUCTANCE' .or. &
5070  obsrv%ObsTypeId=='WETTED-AREA') then
5071  do j = 1, obsrv%indxbnds_count
5072  nn1 = obsrv%indxbnds(j)
5073  if (nn1 < 1 .or. nn1 > this%maxbound) then
5074  write(errmsg, '(a,1x,a,1x,i0,1x,a,1x,i0,a)') &
5075  trim(adjustl(obsrv%ObsTypeId)), &
5076  'lake connection number must be > 0 and <=', this%maxbound, &
5077  '(specified value is ', nn1, ')'
5078  call store_error(errmsg)
5079  end if
5080  end do
5081  else
5082  do j = 1, obsrv%indxbnds_count
5083  nn1 = obsrv%indxbnds(j)
5084  if (nn1 < 1 .or. nn1 > this%nlakes) then
5085  write(errmsg, '(a,1x,a,1x,i0,1x,a,1x,i0,a)') &
5086  trim(adjustl(obsrv%ObsTypeId)), &
5087  ' lake must be > 0 and <=', this%nlakes, &
5088  '(specified value is ', nn1, ')'
5089  call store_error(errmsg)
5090  end if
5091  end do
5092  end if
5093  end do
5094  !
5095  ! -- evaluate if there are any observation errors
5096  if (count_errors() > 0) then
5097  call store_error_unit(this%inunit)
5098  end if
5099  end if
5100  !
5101  return
5102  end subroutine lak_rp_obs

5105  !
5106  ! -- Procedures related to observations (NOT type-bound)
5107  subroutine lak_process_obsid(obsrv, dis, inunitobs, iout)
5108  ! -- This procedure is pointed to by ObsDataType%ProcesssIdPtr. It processes
5109  ! the ID string of an observation definition for LAK package observations.
5110  ! -- dummy
5111  type(observetype), intent(inout) :: obsrv
5112  class(disbasetype), intent(in) :: dis
5113  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: inunitobs
5114  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: iout
5115  ! -- local
5116  integer(I4B) :: nn1, nn2
5117  integer(I4B) :: icol, istart, istop
5118  character(len=LINELENGTH) :: strng
5119  character(len=LENBOUNDNAME) :: bndname
5120  ! formats
5121  !
5122  strng = obsrv%IDstring
5123  ! -- Extract lake number from strng and store it.
5124  ! If 1st item is not an integer(I4B), it should be a
5125  ! lake name--deal with it.
5126  icol = 1
5127  ! -- get lake number or boundary name
5128  call extract_idnum_or_bndname(strng, icol, istart, istop, nn1, bndname)
5129  if (nn1 == namedboundflag) then
5130  obsrv%FeatureName = bndname
5131  else
5132  if (obsrv%ObsTypeId=='LAK' .or. obsrv%ObsTypeId=='CONDUCTANCE' .or. &
5133  obsrv%ObsTypeId=='WETTED-AREA') then
5134  call extract_idnum_or_bndname(strng, icol, istart, istop, nn2, bndname)
5135  if (len_trim(bndname) < 1 .and. nn2 < 0) then
5136  write(errmsg, '(a,1x,a,a,1x,a,1x,a)') &
5137  'For observation type', trim(adjustl(obsrv%ObsTypeId)), &
5138  ', ID given as an integer and not as boundname,',&
5139  'but ID2 (iconn) is missing. Either change ID to valid', &
5140  'boundname or supply valid entry for ID2.'
5141  call store_error(errmsg)
5142  end if
5143  if (nn2 == namedboundflag) then
5144  obsrv%FeatureName = bndname
5145  ! -- reset nn1
5146  nn1 = nn2
5147  else
5148  obsrv%NodeNumber2 = nn2
5149  end if
5150  !! -- store connection number (NodeNumber2)
5151  !obsrv%NodeNumber2 = nn2
5152  endif
5153  endif
5154  ! -- store lake number (NodeNumber)
5155  obsrv%NodeNumber = nn1
5156  !
5157  return
5158  end subroutine lak_process_obsid

5163  subroutine lak_accumulate_chterm(this, ilak, rrate, chratin, chratout)
5164  ! **************************************************************************
5165  ! lak_accumulate_chterm -- Accumulate constant head terms for budget.
5166  ! **************************************************************************
5167  !
5168  ! SPECIFICATIONS:
5169  ! --------------------------------------------------------------------------
5170  ! -- dummy
5171  class(laktype) :: this
5172  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: ilak
5173  real(DP), intent(in) :: rrate
5174  real(DP), intent(inout) :: chratin
5175  real(DP), intent(inout) :: chratout
5176  ! -- locals
5177  real(DP) :: q
5178  ! format
5179  ! code
5180  if (this%iboundpak(ilak) < 0) then
5181  q = -rrate
5182  this%chterm(ilak) = this%chterm(ilak) + q
5183  !
5184  ! -- See if flow is into lake or out of lake.
5185  if (q < dzero) then
5186  !
5187  ! -- Flow is out of lake subtract rate from ratout.
5188  chratout = chratout - q
5189  else
5190  !
5191  ! -- Flow is into lake; add rate to ratin.
5192  chratin = chratin + q
5193  end if
5194  end if

5196  return

5200  subroutine lak_cfupdate(this)
5201  ! ******************************************************************************
5202  ! lak_cfupdate -- Update LAK satcond and package rhs and hcof
5203  ! ******************************************************************************
5204  !
5205  ! SPECIFICATIONS:
5206  ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5207  class(laktype), intent(inout) :: this
5208  integer(I4B) :: j, n, node
5209  real(DP) :: hlak, head, clak, blak
5210  ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5211  !
5212  ! -- Return if no lak lakes
5213  if(this%nbound.eq.0) return
5214  !
5215  ! -- Calculate hcof and rhs for each lak entry
5216  do n = 1, this%nlakes
5217  hlak = this%xnewpak(n)
5218  do j = this%idxlakeconn(n), this%idxlakeconn(n+1)-1
5219  node = this%cellid(j)
5220  head = this%xnew(node)
5221 
5222  this%hcof(j) = dzero
5223  this%rhs(j) = dzero
5224  !
5225  ! -- set bound, hcof, and rhs components
5226  call this%lak_calculate_conn_conductance(n, j, hlak, head, clak)
5227  this%simcond(j) = clak
5228 
5229  this%bound(2,j) = clak
5230 
5231  blak = this%bound(3,j)
5232 
5233  this%hcof(j) = -clak
5234  !
5235  ! -- fill rhs
5236  if (hlak < blak) then
5237  this%rhs(j) = -clak * blak
5238  else
5239  this%rhs(j) = -clak * hlak
5240  end if
5241  end do
5242  end do
5243  !
5244  ! -- Return
5245  return
5246  end subroutine lak_cfupdate

5280  subroutine lak_solve(this, update)
5281  ! **************************************************************************
5282  ! lak_solve -- Solve for lake stage
5283  ! **************************************************************************
5284  !
5285  ! SPECIFICATIONS:
5286  ! --------------------------------------------------------------------------
5287  use tdismodule,only:delt
5288  logical, intent(in), optional :: update
5289  ! -- dummy
5290  class(laktype), intent(inout) :: this
5291  ! -- local
5292  logical :: lupdate
5293  integer(I4B) :: i
5294  integer(I4B) :: j
5295  integer(I4B) :: n
5296  integer(I4B) :: iicnvg
5297  integer(I4B) :: iter
5298  integer(I4B) :: maxiter
5299  integer(I4B) :: ncnv
5300  integer(I4B) :: idry
5301  integer(I4B) :: idry1
5302  integer(I4B) :: igwfnode
5303  integer(I4B) :: ibflg
5304  integer(I4B) :: idhp
5305  real(DP) :: hlak
5306  real(DP) :: hlak0
5307  real(DP) :: v0
5308  real(DP) :: v1
5309  real(DP) :: head
5310  real(DP) :: ra
5311  real(DP) :: ro
5312  real(DP) :: qinf
5313  real(DP) :: ex
5314  real(DP) :: ev
5315  real(DP) :: outinf
5316  real(DP) :: qlakgw
5317  real(DP) :: qlakgw1
5318  real(DP) :: gwfhcof
5319  real(DP) :: gwfrhs
5320  real(DP) :: avail
5321  real(DP) :: resid
5322  real(DP) :: resid1
5323  real(DP) :: residb
5324  real(DP) :: wr
5325  real(DP) :: derv
5326  real(DP) :: dh
5327  real(DP) :: adh
5328  real(DP) :: adh0
5329  real(DP) :: delh
5330  real(DP) :: ts
5331 ! --------------------------------------------------------------------------
5332  !
5333  ! -- set lupdate
5334  if (present(update)) then
5335  lupdate = update
5336  else
5337  lupdate = .true.
5338  end if
5339  !
5340  ! -- initialize
5341  avail = dzero
5342  delh = this%delh
5343  !
5344  ! -- initialize
5345  do n = 1, this%nlakes
5346  this%ncncvr(n) = 0
5347  this%surfin(n) = dzero
5348  this%surfout(n) = dzero
5349  this%surfout1(n) = dzero
5350  if (this%xnewpak(n) < this%lakebot(n)) then
5351  this%xnewpak(n) = this%lakebot(n)
5352  end if
5353  if (this%gwfiss /= 0) then
5354  this%xoldpak(n) = this%xnewpak(n)
5355  end if
5356  ! -- lake iteration items
5357  this%iseepc(n) = 0
5358  this%idhc(n) = 0
5359  this%en1(n) = this%lakebot(n)
5360  call this%lak_calculate_residual(n, this%en1(n), this%r1(n))
5361  this%en2(n) = this%laketop(n)
5362  call this%lak_calculate_residual(n, this%en2(n), this%r2(n))
5363  end do
5364  do n = 1, this%noutlets
5365  this%simoutrate(n) = dzero
5366  end do
5367  !
5368  ! -- sum up inflows from mover inflows
5369  do n = 1, this%nlakes
5370  call this%lak_calculate_outlet_inflow(n, this%surfin(n))
5371  end do
5372  !
5373  ! -- sum up overland runoff, inflows, and external flows into lake
5374  ! (includes lake volume)
5375  do n = 1, this%nlakes
5376  hlak0 = this%xoldpak(n)
5377  call this%lak_calculate_runoff(n, ro)
5378  call this%lak_calculate_inflow(n, qinf)
5379  call this%lak_calculate_external(n, ex)
5380  ! --
5381  call this%lak_calculate_vol(n, hlak0, v0)
5382  this%flwin(n) = this%surfin(n) + ro + qinf + ex + v0 / delt
5383  end do
5384  !
5385  ! -- sum up inflows from upstream outlets
5386  do n = 1, this%nlakes
5387  call this%lak_calculate_outlet_inflow(n, outinf)
5388  this%flwin(n) = this%flwin(n) + outinf
5389  end do
5390 
5391  iicnvg = 0
5392  maxiter = 150
5393 
5394  ! -- outer loop
5395  converge: do iter = 1, maxiter
5396  ncnv = 0
5397  do n = 1, this%nlakes
5398  if (this%ncncvr(n) == 0) ncnv = 1
5399  end do
5400  if (iter == maxiter) ncnv = 0
5401  if (ncnv == 0) iicnvg = 1
5402 
5403  ! -- initialize variables
5404  do n = 1, this%nlakes
5405  this%evap(n) = dzero
5406  this%precip(n) = dzero
5407  this%precip1(n) = dzero
5408  this%seep(n) = dzero
5409  this%seep1(n) = dzero
5410  this%evap(n) = dzero
5411  this%evap1(n) = dzero
5412  this%evapo(n) = dzero
5413  this%withr(n) = dzero
5414  this%withr1(n) = dzero
5415  this%flwiter(n) = this%flwin(n)
5416  this%flwiter1(n) = this%flwin(n)
5417  if (this%gwfiss /= 0) then
5418  this%flwiter(n) = dep20 !1.D+10
5419  this%flwiter1(n) = dep20 !1.D+10
5420  end if
5421  end do
5422 
5423  estseep: do i = 1, 2
5424  lakseep: do n = 1, this%nlakes
5425  ! -- skip inactive lakes
5426  if (this%iboundpak(n) == 0) then
5427  cycle lakseep
5428  end if
5429  ! - set xoldpak to xnewpak if steady-state
5430  if (this%gwfiss /= 0) then
5431  this%xoldpak(n) = this%xnewpak(n)
5432  end if
5433  hlak = this%xnewpak(n)
5434  calcconnseep: do j = this%idxlakeconn(n), this%idxlakeconn(n+1)-1
5435  igwfnode = this%cellid(j)
5436  head = this%xnew(igwfnode)
5437  if (this%ncncvr(n) /= 2) then
5438  if (this%ibound(igwfnode) > 0) then
5439  call this%lak_estimate_conn_exchange(i, n, j, idry, hlak, &
5440  head, qlakgw, &
5441  this%flwiter(n), &
5442  gwfhcof, gwfrhs)
5443  call this%lak_estimate_conn_exchange(i, n, j, idry1, hlak+delh,&
5444  head, qlakgw1, &
5445  this%flwiter1(n))
5446  !
5447  ! -- add to gwf matrix
5448  if (ncnv == 0 .and. i == 2) then
5449  if (j == this%maxbound) then
5450  this%ncncvr(n) = 2
5451  end if
5452  if (idry /= 1) then
5453  this%hcof(j) = gwfhcof
5454  this%rhs(j) = gwfrhs
5455  else
5456  this%hcof(j) = dzero
5457  this%rhs(j) = qlakgw
5458  end if
5459  end if
5460  if (i == 2) then
5461  this%seep(n) = this%seep(n) + qlakgw
5462  this%seep1(n) = this%seep1(n) + qlakgw1
5463  end if
5464  end if
5465  end if
5466 
5467  end do calcconnseep
5468  end do lakseep
5469  end do estseep
5470 
5471  laklevel: do n = 1, this%nlakes
5472  ibflg = 0
5473  hlak = this%xnewpak(n)
5474  if (iter < maxiter) then
5475  this%stageiter(n) = this%xnewpak(n)
5476  end if
5477  call this%lak_calculate_rainfall(n, hlak, ra)
5478  this%precip(n) = ra
5479  this%flwiter(n) = this%flwiter(n) + ra
5480  call this%lak_calculate_rainfall(n, hlak+delh, ra)
5481  this%precip1(n) = ra
5482  this%flwiter1(n) = this%flwiter1(n) + ra
5483  !
5484  ! -- limit withdrawals to lake inflows and lake storage
5485  call this%lak_calculate_withdrawal(n, this%flwiter(n), wr)
5486  this%withr = wr
5487  call this%lak_calculate_withdrawal(n, this%flwiter1(n), wr)
5488  this%withr1 = wr
5489  !
5490  ! -- limit evaporation to lake inflows and lake storage
5491  call this%lak_calculate_evaporation(n, hlak, this%flwiter(n), ev)
5492  this%evap(n) = ev
5493  call this%lak_calculate_evaporation(n, hlak+delh, this%flwiter1(n), ev)
5494  this%evap1(n) = ev
5495  !
5496  ! -- no outlet flow if evaporation consumes all water
5497  call this%lak_calculate_outlet_outflow(n, hlak+delh, &
5498  this%flwiter1(n), &
5499  this%surfout1(n))
5500  call this%lak_calculate_outlet_outflow(n, hlak, this%flwiter(n), &
5501  this%surfout(n))
5502  !
5503  ! -- update the surface inflow values
5504  call this%lak_calculate_outlet_inflow(n, this%surfin(n))
5505  !
5506  !
5507  if (ncnv == 1) then
5508  if (this%iboundpak(n) > 0 .and. lupdate .eqv. .true.) then
5509  !
5510  ! -- recalculate flwin
5511  hlak0 = this%xoldpak(n)
5512  call this%lak_calculate_vol(n, hlak0, v0)
5513  call this%lak_calculate_runoff(n, ro)
5514  call this%lak_calculate_inflow(n, qinf)
5515  call this%lak_calculate_external(n, ex)
5516  this%flwin(n) = this%surfin(n) + ro + qinf + ex + v0 / delt
5517  !
5518  ! -- compute new lake stage using Newton's method
5519  resid = this%precip(n) + this%evap(n) + this%withr(n) + ro + &
5520  qinf + ex + this%surfin(n) + &
5521  this%surfout(n) + this%seep(n)
5522  resid1 = this%precip1(n) + this%evap1(n) + this%withr1(n) + ro + &
5523  qinf + ex + this%surfin(n) + &
5524  this%surfout1(n) + this%seep1(n)
5525 
5526  !call this%lak_calculate_residual(n, this%xnewpak(n), residb)
5527  !
5528  ! -- add storage changes for transient stress periods
5529  hlak = this%xnewpak(n)
5530  if (this%gwfiss /= 1) then
5531  call this%lak_calculate_vol(n, hlak, v1)
5532  resid = resid + (v0 - v1) / delt
5533  call this%lak_calculate_vol(n, hlak+delh, v1)
5534  resid1 = resid1 + (v0 - v1) / delt
5535  !else
5536  ! call this%lak_calculate_vol(n, hlak, v1)
5537  ! resid = resid - v1 / delt
5538  ! call this%lak_calculate_vol(n, hlak+delh, v1)
5539  ! resid1 = resid1 - v1 / delt
5540  end if
5541 
5542  !
5543  ! -- determine the derivative and the stage change
5544  if (abs(resid1-resid) > dzero) then
5545  derv = (resid1 - resid) / delh
5546  dh = dzero
5547  if (abs(derv) > dprec) then
5548  dh = resid / derv
5549  end if
5550  else
5551  if (resid < dzero) then
5552  resid = dzero
5553  end if
5554  call this%lak_vol2stage(n, resid, dh)
5555  dh = hlak - dh
5556  this%ncncvr(n) = 1
5557  end if
5558  !
5559  ! -- determine if the updated stage is outside the endpoints
5560  ts = hlak-dh
5561  if (iter == 1) this%dh0(n) = dh
5562  adh = abs(dh)
5563  adh0 = abs(this%dh0(n))
5564  if ((ts >= this%en2(n)) .or. (ts <= this%en1(n))) then
5565  ! -- use bisection if dh is increasing or updated stage is below the
5566  ! bottom of the lake
5567  if ((adh > adh0) .or. (ts-this%lakebot(n)) < dprec) then
5568  ibflg = 1
5569  ts = dhalf * (this%en1(n) + this%en2(n))
5570  call this%lak_calculate_residual(n, ts, residb)
5571  dh = hlak - ts
5572  end if
5573  end if
5574  !
5575  ! -- set seep0 on the first lake iteration
5576  if (iter == 1) then
5577  this%seep0(n) = this%seep(n)
5578  end if
5579  !
5580  ! -- check for slow convergence
5581  if (this%seep(n)*this%seep0(n) < dprec) then
5582  this%iseepc(n) = this%iseepc(n) + 1
5583  else
5584  this%iseepc(n) = 0
5585  end if
5586  ! -- determine of convergence is slow and oscillating
5587  idhp = 0
5588  if (dh*this%dh0(n) < dprec) idhp = 1
5589  ! -- determine if stage change is increasing
5590  adh = abs(dh)
5591  if (adh > adh0) idhp = 1
5592  ! -- increment idhc convergence flag
5593  if (idhp == 1) then
5594  this%idhc(n) = this%idhc(n) + 1
5595  end if
5596  !
5597  ! -- switch to bisection when the Newton-Raphson method oscillates
5598  ! or when convergence is slow
5599  if (ibflg == 1) then
5600  if (this%iseepc(n) > 7 .or. this%idhc(n) > 12) then
5601  ibflg = 1
5602  ts = dhalf * (this%en1(n) + this%en2(n))
5603  call this%lak_calculate_residual(n, ts, residb)
5604  dh = hlak - ts
5605  end if
5606  end if
5607  if (ibflg == 1) then
5608  ! -- change end points
5609  ! -- root is between r1 and residb
5610  if (this%r1(n)*residb < dzero) then
5611  this%en2(n) = ts
5612  this%r2(n) = residb
5613  ! -- root is between fp and f2
5614  else
5615  this%en1(n) = ts
5616  this%r1(n) = residb
5617  end if
5618  end if
5619  else
5620  dh = dzero
5621  end if
5622  !
5623  ! -- update lake stage
5624  hlak = hlak - dh
5625  if (hlak < this%lakebot(n)) then
5626  hlak = this%lakebot(n)
5627  end if
5628  if (abs(dh) < delh) then
5629  this%ncncvr(n) = 1
5630  end if
5631  this%xnewpak(n) = hlak
5632  !
5633  ! -- save iterates for lake
5634  this%seep0(n) = this%seep(n)
5635  this%dh0(n) = dh
5636  end if
5637  end do laklevel
5638 
5639  if (iicnvg == 1) exit converge
5640 
5641  end do converge
5642  !
5643  ! -- Mover terms: store outflow after diversion loss
5644  ! as qformvr and reduce outflow (qd)
5645  ! by how much was actually sent to the mover
5646  if (this%imover == 1) then
5647  do n = 1, this%noutlets
5648  call this%pakmvrobj%accumulate_qformvr(n, -this%simoutrate(n))
5649  end do
5650  end if
5651  !
5652  ! -- return
5653  return
5654  end subroutine lak_solve

5657  subroutine lak_calculate_available(this, n, hlak, avail, &
5658  ra, ro, qinf, ex, headp)
5659  ! **************************************************************************
5660  ! lak_calculate_available -- Calculate the available volumetric rate for
5661  ! a lake given a passed stage
5662  ! **************************************************************************
5663  !
5664  ! SPECIFICATIONS:
5665  ! --------------------------------------------------------------------------
5666  use tdismodule,only:delt
5667  ! -- dummy
5668  class(laktype), intent(inout) :: this
5669  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: n
5670  real(DP), intent(in) :: hlak
5671  real(DP), intent(inout) :: avail
5672  real(DP), intent(inout) :: ra
5673  real(DP), intent(inout) :: ro
5674  real(DP), intent(inout) :: qinf
5675  real(DP), intent(inout) :: ex
5676  real(DP), intent(in), optional :: headp
5677  ! -- local
5678  integer(I4B) :: j
5679  integer(I4B) :: idry
5680  integer(I4B) :: igwfnode
5681  real(DP) :: hp
5682  real(DP) :: head
5683  real(DP) :: qlakgw
5684  real(DP) :: v0
5685  ! code
5686  !
5687  ! -- set hp
5688  if (present(headp)) then
5689  hp = headp
5690  else
5691  hp = dzero
5692  end if
5693  !
5694  ! -- initialize
5695  avail = dzero
5696  !
5697  ! -- calculate the aquifer sources to the lake
5698  do j = this%idxlakeconn(n), this%idxlakeconn(n+1)-1
5699  igwfnode = this%cellid(j)
5700  if (this%ibound(igwfnode) == 0) cycle
5701  head = this%xnew(igwfnode) + hp
5702  call this%lak_estimate_conn_exchange(1, n, j, idry, hlak, head, qlakgw, avail)
5703  end do
5704  !
5705  ! -- add rainfall
5706  call this%lak_calculate_rainfall(n, hlak, ra)
5707  avail = avail + ra
5708  !
5709  ! -- calculate runoff
5710  call this%lak_calculate_runoff(n, ro)
5711  avail = avail + ro
5712  !
5713  ! -- calculate inflow
5714  call this%lak_calculate_inflow(n, qinf)
5715  avail = avail + qinf
5716  !
5717  ! -- calculate external flow terms
5718  call this%lak_calculate_external(n, ex)
5719  avail = avail + ex
5720  !
5721  ! -- calculate volume available in storage
5722  call this%lak_calculate_vol(n, this%xoldpak(n), v0)
5723  avail = avail + v0 / delt
5724  !
5725  ! -- return
5726  return
5727  end subroutine lak_calculate_available

5729 
5730  subroutine lak_calculate_residual(this, n, hlak, resid, headp)
5731  ! **************************************************************************
5732  ! lak_calculate_residual -- Calculate the residual for a lake given a
5733  ! passed stage
5734  ! **************************************************************************
5735  !
5736  ! SPECIFICATIONS:
5737  ! --------------------------------------------------------------------------
5738  use tdismodule,only:delt
5739  ! -- dummy
5740  class(laktype), intent(inout) :: this
5741  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: n
5742  real(DP), intent(in) :: hlak
5743  real(DP), intent(inout) :: resid
5744  real(DP), intent(in), optional :: headp
5745  ! -- local
5746  integer(I4B) :: j
5747  integer(I4B) :: idry
5748  integer(I4B) :: igwfnode
5749  real(DP) :: hp
5750  real(DP) :: avail
5751  real(DP) :: head
5752  real(DP) :: ra
5753  real(DP) :: ro
5754  real(DP) :: qinf
5755  real(DP) :: ex
5756  real(DP) :: ev
5757  real(DP) :: wr
5758  real(DP) :: sout
5759  real(DP) :: sin
5760  real(DP) :: qlakgw
5761  real(DP) :: seep
5762  real(DP) :: hlak0
5763  real(DP) :: v0
5764  real(DP) :: v1
5765  !
5766  ! -- code
5767  !
5768  ! -- set hp
5769  if (present(headp)) then
5770  hp = headp
5771  else
5772  hp = dzero
5773  end if
5774  !
5775  ! -- initialize
5776  resid = dzero
5777  avail = dzero
5778  seep = dzero
5779  !
5780  ! -- calculate the available water
5781  call this%lak_calculate_available(n, hlak, avail, &
5782  ra, ro, qinf, ex, hp)
5783  !
5784  ! -- calculate groundwater seepage
5785  do j = this%idxlakeconn(n), this%idxlakeconn(n+1)-1
5786  igwfnode = this%cellid(j)
5787  if (this%ibound(igwfnode) == 0) cycle
5788  head = this%xnew(igwfnode) + hp
5789  call this%lak_estimate_conn_exchange(2, n, j, idry, hlak, head, qlakgw, avail)
5790  seep = seep + qlakgw
5791  end do
5792  !
5793  ! -- limit withdrawals to lake inflows and lake storage
5794  call this%lak_calculate_withdrawal(n, avail, wr)
5795  !
5796  ! -- limit evaporation to lake inflows and lake storage
5797  call this%lak_calculate_evaporation(n, hlak, avail, ev)
5798  !
5799  ! -- no outlet flow if evaporation consumes all water
5800  call this%lak_calculate_outlet_outflow(n, hlak, avail, sout)
5801  !
5802  ! -- update the surface inflow values
5803  call this%lak_calculate_outlet_inflow(n, sin)
5804  !
5805  ! -- calculate residual
5806  resid = ra + ev + wr + ro + qinf + ex + sin + sout + seep
5807  !
5808  ! -- include storage
5809  if (this%gwfiss /= 1) then
5810  hlak0 = this%xoldpak(n)
5811  call this%lak_calculate_vol(n, hlak0, v0)
5812  call this%lak_calculate_vol(n, hlak, v1)
5813  resid = resid + (v0 - v1) / delt
5814  end if
5815  !
5816  ! -- return
5817  return
5818  end subroutine lak_calculate_residual

5927  naux = 0

5929  this%name_model, &
5930  this%packName, &

5940  naux = 0

5944  this%name_model, &
5945  this%packName, &

5950  text = ' EXT-INFLOW'

5953  naux = 0

5966  naux = 0

6071  subroutine lak_fill_budobj(this)
6072 ! ******************************************************************************
6073 ! lak_fill_budobj -- copy flow terms into this%budobj
6074 ! ******************************************************************************
6075 !
6076 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
6077 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6078  ! -- modules
6079  ! -- dummy
6080  class(laktype) :: this
6081  ! -- local
6082  integer(I4B) :: naux
6083  real(DP), dimension(:), allocatable :: auxvartmp
6084  !integer(I4B) :: i
6085  integer(I4B) :: j
6086  integer(I4B) :: n
6087  integer(I4B) :: n1
6088  integer(I4B) :: n2
6089  integer(I4B) :: ii
6090  integer(I4B) :: jj
6091  integer(I4B) :: idx
6092  integer(I4B) :: nlen
6093  real(DP) :: v, v1
6094  real(DP) :: q
6095  ! -- formats
6096 ! -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6097  !
6098  ! -- initialize counter
6099  idx = 0
6100 
6101 
6102  ! -- FLOW JA FACE
6103  nlen = 0
6104  do n = 1, this%noutlets
6105  if (this%lakein(n) > 0 .and. this%lakeout(n) > 0) then
6106  nlen = nlen + 1
6107  end if
6108  end do
6109  if (nlen > 0) then
6110  idx = idx + 1
6111  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%reset(2 * nlen)
6112  do n = 1, this%noutlets
6113  n1 = this%lakein(n)
6114  n2 = this%lakeout(n)
6115  if (n1 > 0 .and. n2 > 0) then
6116  q = this%simoutrate(n)
6117  if (this%imover == 1) then
6118  q = q + this%pakmvrobj%get_qtomvr(n)
6119  end if
6120  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%update_term(n1, n2, q)
6121  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%update_term(n2, n1, -q)
6122  end if
6123  end do
6124  end if
6125 
6126 
6127  ! -- GWF (LEAKAGE)
6128  idx = idx + 1
6129  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%reset(this%maxbound)
6130  do n = 1, this%nlakes
6131  do j = this%idxlakeconn(n), this%idxlakeconn(n + 1) - 1
6132  n2 = this%cellid(j)
6133  q = this%qleak(j)
6134  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%update_term(n, n2, q, this%qauxcbc)
6135  end do
6136  end do
6137 
6138 
6139  ! -- RAIN
6140  idx = idx + 1
6141  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%reset(this%nlakes)
6142  do n = 1, this%nlakes
6143  q = this%precip(n)
6144  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%update_term(n, n, q)
6145  end do
6146 
6147 
6148  ! -- EVAPORATION
6149  idx = idx + 1
6150  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%reset(this%nlakes)
6151  do n = 1, this%nlakes
6152  q = this%evap(n)
6153  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%update_term(n, n, q)
6154  end do
6155 
6156 
6157  ! -- RUNOFF
6158  idx = idx + 1
6159  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%reset(this%nlakes)
6160  do n = 1, this%nlakes
6161  q = this%runoff(n)
6162  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%update_term(n, n, q)
6163  end do
6164 
6165 
6166  ! -- INFLOW
6167  idx = idx + 1
6168  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%reset(this%nlakes)
6169  do n = 1, this%nlakes
6170  q = this%inflow(n)
6171  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%update_term(n, n, q)
6172  end do
6173 
6174 
6175  ! -- WITHDRAWAL
6176  idx = idx + 1
6177  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%reset(this%nlakes)
6178  do n = 1, this%nlakes
6179  q = this%withr(n)
6180  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%update_term(n, n, q)
6181  end do
6182 
6183 
6184  ! -- EXTERNAL OUTFLOW
6185  idx = idx + 1
6186  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%reset(this%nlakes)
6187  do n = 1, this%nlakes
6188  call this%lak_get_external_outlet(n, q)
6189  ! subtract tomover from external outflow
6190  call this%lak_get_external_mover(n, v)
6191  q = q + v
6192  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%update_term(n, n, q)
6193  end do
6194 
6195 
6196  ! -- STORAGE
6197  idx = idx + 1
6198  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%reset(this%nlakes)
6199  do n = 1, this%nlakes
6200  call this%lak_calculate_vol(n, this%xnewpak(n), v1)
6201  q = this%qsto(n)
6202  this%qauxcbc(1) = v1
6203  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%update_term(n, n, q, this%qauxcbc)
6204  end do
6205 
6206 
6207  ! -- CONSTANT FLOW
6208  idx = idx + 1
6209  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%reset(this%nlakes)
6210  do n = 1, this%nlakes
6211  q = this%chterm(n)
6212  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%update_term(n, n, q)
6213  end do
6214 
6215 
6216  ! -- MOVER
6217  if (this%imover == 1) then
6218 
6219  ! -- FROM MOVER
6220  idx = idx + 1
6221  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%reset(this%nlakes)
6222  do n = 1, this%nlakes
6223  q = this%pakmvrobj%get_qfrommvr(n)
6224  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%update_term(n, n, q)
6225  end do
6226 
6227 
6228  ! -- TO MOVER
6229  idx = idx + 1
6230  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%reset(this%noutlets)
6231  do n = 1, this%noutlets
6232  n1 = this%lakein(n)
6233  q = this%pakmvrobj%get_qtomvr(n)
6234  if (q > dzero) then
6235  q = -q
6236  end if
6237  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%update_term(n1, n1, q)
6238  end do
6239 
6240  end if
6241 
6242 
6243  ! -- AUXILIARY VARIABLES
6244  naux = this%naux
6245  if (naux > 0) then
6246  idx = idx + 1
6247  allocate(auxvartmp(naux))
6248  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%reset(this%nlakes)
6249  do n = 1, this%nlakes
6250  q = dzero
6251  do jj = 1, naux
6252  ii = n
6253  auxvartmp(jj) = this%lauxvar(jj, ii)
6254  end do
6255  call this%budobj%budterm(idx)%update_term(n, n, q, auxvartmp)
6256  end do
6257  deallocate(auxvartmp)
6258  end if
6259  !
6260  ! --Terms are filled, now accumulate them for this time step
6261  call this%budobj%accumulate_terms()
6262  !
6263  ! -- return
6264  return
6265  end subroutine lak_fill_budobj

6368 
6369  subroutine lak_calculate_density_exchange(this, iconn, stage, head, cond, &
6370  botl, flow, gwfhcof, gwfrhs)
6371 ! ******************************************************************************
6372 ! lak_calculate_density_exchange -- Calculate the groundwater-lake density
6373 ! exchange terms.
6374 !
6375 ! -- Arguments are as follows:
6376 ! iconn : lak-gwf connection number
6377 ! stage : lake stage
6378 ! head : gwf head
6379 ! cond : conductance
6380 ! botl : bottom elevation of this connection
6381 ! flow : calculated flow, updated here with density terms
6382 ! gwfhcof : gwf head coefficient, updated here with density terms
6383 ! gwfrhs : gwf right-hand-side value, updated here with density terms
6384 !
6385 ! -- Member variable used here
6386 ! denseterms : shape (3, MAXBOUND), filled by buoyancy package
6387 ! col 1 is relative density of lake (denselak / denseref)
6388 ! col 2 is relative density of gwf cell (densegwf / denseref)
6389 ! col 3 is elevation of gwf cell
6390 !
6391 ! ******************************************************************************
6392 !
6393 ! SPECIFICATIONS:
6394 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6395  ! -- dummy
6396  class(laktype),intent(inout) :: this
6397  integer(I4B), intent(in) :: iconn
6398  real(DP), intent(in) :: stage
6399  real(DP), intent(in) :: head
6400  real(DP), intent(in) :: cond
6401  real(DP), intent(in) :: botl
6402  real(DP), intent(inout) :: flow
6403  real(DP), intent(inout) :: gwfhcof
6404  real(DP), intent(inout) :: gwfrhs
6405  ! -- local
6406  real(DP) :: ss
6407  real(DP) :: hh
6408  real(DP) :: havg
6409  real(DP) :: rdenselak
6410  real(DP) :: rdensegwf
6411  real(DP) :: rdenseavg
6412  real(DP) :: elevlak
6413  real(DP) :: elevgwf
6414  real(DP) :: elevavg
6415  real(DP) :: d1
6416  real(DP) :: d2
6417  logical :: stage_below_bot
6418  logical :: head_below_bot
6419  ! -- formats
6420 ! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6421  !
6422  ! -- Set lak density to lak density or gwf density
6423  if (stage >= botl) then
6424  ss = stage
6425  stage_below_bot = .false.
6426  rdenselak = this%denseterms(1, iconn) ! lak rel density
6427  else
6428  ss = botl
6429  stage_below_bot = .true.
6430  rdenselak = this%denseterms(2, iconn) ! gwf rel density
6431  end if
6432  !
6433  ! -- set hh to head or botl
6434  if (head >= botl) then
6435  hh = head
6436  head_below_bot = .false.
6437  rdensegwf = this%denseterms(2, iconn) ! gwf rel density
6438  else
6439  hh = botl
6440  head_below_bot = .true.
6441  rdensegwf = this%denseterms(1, iconn) ! lak rel density
6442  end if
6443  !
6444  ! -- todo: hack because denseterms not updated in a cf calculation
6445  if (rdensegwf == dzero) return
6446  !
6447  ! -- Update flow
6448  if (stage_below_bot .and. head_below_bot) then
6449  !
6450  ! -- flow is zero, so no terms are updated
6451  !
6452  else
6453  !
6454  ! -- calulate average relative density
6455  rdenseavg = dhalf * (rdenselak + rdensegwf)
6456  !
6457  ! -- Add contribution of first density term:
6458  ! cond * (denseavg/denseref - 1) * (hgwf - hlak)
6459  d1 = cond * (rdenseavg - done)
6460  gwfhcof = gwfhcof - d1
6461  gwfrhs = gwfrhs - d1 * ss
6462  d1 = d1 * (hh - ss)
6463  flow = flow + d1
6464  !
6465  ! -- Add second density term if stage and head not below bottom
6466  if (.not. stage_below_bot .and. .not. head_below_bot) then
6467  !
6468  ! -- Add contribution of second density term:
6469  ! cond * (havg - elevavg) * (densegwf - denselak) / denseref
6470  elevgwf = this%denseterms(3, iconn)
6471  if (this%ictype(iconn) == 0 .or. this%ictype(iconn) == 3) then
6472  ! -- vertical or embedded vertical connection
6473  elevlak = botl
6474  else
6475  ! -- horizontal or embedded horizontal connection
6476  elevlak = elevgwf
6477  end if
6478  elevavg = dhalf * (elevlak + elevgwf)
6479  havg = dhalf * (hh + ss)
6480  d2 = cond * (havg - elevavg) * (rdensegwf - rdenselak)
6481  gwfrhs = gwfrhs + d2
6482  flow = flow + d2
6483  end if
6484  end if
6485  !
6486  ! -- return
6487  return
6488  end subroutine lak_calculate_density_exchange
6489 
6490 
6491 end module lakmodule
